title: orange cake
directions: Bake in tube or spring-form pan at 350° until done.

title: pineapple-nut sheet cake
directions: Mix everything in a bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased and floured tube pan for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; chill overnight.
Fold in apples, grapes and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: egg substitute
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender; whirl.
Yield is equivalent of 1 egg.

title: homemade orange refresher
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a blender container and process at high speed.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, blending until slushy.
Serve immediately. Yields 4 servings.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Cook until done.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolved 1 cup warm water and jello.
Add other ingredients and gel.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and sugar for topping.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: egg rolls
directions: Fry meat until done.
Drain grease.
Set aside.
Boil cabbage until soft.
Boil carrots until soft.
Boil glass noodles until soft.
Mix all ingredients.
Place egg roll skin with one point toward you.
Spoon 1/4 cup of filling diagonally across and just below center of skin.
Fold bottom point of skin over filling; tuck point under filling.
Fold side corners over, forming envelope.
Roll up toward remaining corner.
Moisten point and press firmly to seal.
Repeat with remaining egg roll skin and filling.
Fry rolls, a few at a time, in deep hot oil (365°) for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: brandy cream pie
directions: For the crust, crush enough Zwieback to make 1 1/2 cups fine crumbs.
Mix them with powdered sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Press mixture evenly on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: corn bisquits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Melt butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 inch pan. Mix bisquick and corn; stir until dough forms. Knead about 15 times on a floured surface. Roll into 6x10 inch rectangle and cut into 1x3 inch strips. Dip each strip in butter covering all sides and arrange in single layer. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato fritters
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat at 375°.
Fry for 6 minutes or until done.
Drain.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water, celery, onions and salt. Remove chicken and dice.
Save broth for other soup.
Put chopped, drained broccoli in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients with diced chicken and put on top of broccoli. Sprinkle top with crushed French onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey lasagna(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable oil.

title: barbi's elegant chicken for eight
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole with broken up beef and potatoes.
Halve chicken breasts and wrap each in bacon. Arrange among potatoes.
Blend soup and cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with green salad, vegetables and popovers.

title: potato pie
directions: Mix and
pour
in well greased pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: hamburger and chili pepper casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Drain; add salt and pepper, chili powder, peppers and can of soup.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top and put in moderate oven.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: rouladen (stuffed beef rolls)
directions: Have butcher slice steaks thin against the grain; if too thick, pound them thinner.
Lay flat.
Salt and pepper.
Put bacon lengthwise on meat.
Add thin sliced dill pickles.
Add thin sliced onion.
Roll jelly roll fashion into cylinder.
Tie rolls with kitchen string or cord.

title: clam dip
directions: Cream cheese until soft; add clam juice and mix well.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Add clams and chill. Serve as dip with your favorite chips.

title: citrus glaze
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.
Pour into jar and cover tightly.
Cool and refrigerate.
Baste or pour over chicken, ribs or hamburgers.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain green beans.
Add to meat mixture.
Mix 3 kinds soup together.
Pour over meat and bean mixture in 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Arrange Tater Tots (frozen) to cover top of casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: meat 'n potatoes
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic; drain fat.
Stir in tomato paste, broth, salt, oregano and pepper.

title: vegetable pulao
directions: Grind together 3 cloves of garlic, 4 green chilies, and a small piece of ginger.
Season oil with cardamom and cloves, add chopped onions, and fry until light brown.
Add the ground spices and fry until oil separates.
Add vegetables along with turmeric and coriander powder.
Fry for 2 mins.
Add enough water to boil veggies for 5 minutes.
Half boil rice.
Remove the starch from the rice and add it to the vegetables and mix well.
Add a few leaves of mint and keep it on the stove over low flame for 3 mins. Serve hot with raitha.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Lay wafer in bottom of each cupcake paper.
Fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Lay wafer on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry filling.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and 2 chocolate squares on low heat.
Add dry ingredients to the chocolate.
Add eggs and vanilla.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pan.
Place remaining ingredients in blender on high for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Wait 5 minutes to eat.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt in a large bowl.
Combine
milk
and
butter
in a small saucepan. Heat over low heat until liquid is warm (butter does not need to
melt). Gradually
add
to
dry
ingredients
and beat two minutes at medium speed of electric mixer scraping bowl often. Add eggs
and beat
well.
Beat in additional flour to make a soft dough
(do this
with
wooden spoon if you do not have a heavy-duty mixer).

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add milk.
Break bread into mixture.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake in casserole dish in 400° oven approximately 1/2 hour or until done and slightly brown on top.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and powdered sugar in mixer until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, salt and pecans.
Remove from mixer and stir in pastry flour by hand being careful not to overmix.
Form into football shapes about the size of small walnuts and place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 10 - 12 minutes or until just beginning to get the slightest bit colored on the bottom.
Remove upon the first sign of color and set on a rack to cool.
When cool enough to touch, place in a bowl with powdered sugar on top and bottom and toss gently.
Occasionally toss with sugar while cooling, trying to get as much sugar as possible to stick.
When cold, place cookies in airtight container and cover until read to serve.
Yield:
50 cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, onion, pepper, salt and pineapple. Mix altogether.
Form into 1 large ball or 2 small ones.
Let chill, then roll in pecans.

title: twinky cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add vanilla, sugar and salt gradually to beaten eggs.
Heat milk and butter to boiling; add to egg mixture. Then add flour and baking powder.
Bake in a wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool; remove and slice in half.

title: cheese balls(dutch recipe)
directions: Blend all ingredients. Shape into ball and roll in chopped walnuts or dried beef.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fourth of july cheese tidbits
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Form into balls, place on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork into crisscross fashion.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen before cooked.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, water chestnuts, peas and onion in order, in a glass bowl.
Cover with a layer of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons sugar on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage and vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat and flour.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine flour with 1/4 cup water; stir about 1/2 to 1 cup cooking liquid into mixture and gradually stir into soup.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes. Add sausage and continue cooking 2 minutes.

title: ritz cracker snacks
directions: Cook dates, nuts and Eagle Brand milk until thick.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Mix 2 to 3 cups of confectioners sugar with margarine to make a good spreading consistency; add vanilla. "Dollop" a small amount of this mixture on each cracker.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping until thoroughly blended.
Spoon into crust and chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: easy crab dip
directions: Place cream cheese in a dish; put crab meat over.
Place sauce to taste on top and serve with crackers.

title: mayonnaise cookies
directions: Cream together the mayonnaise and sugar, then add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Form into balls, then press with bottom of a fancy glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken breast florentine
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add spinach, garlic and pepper. Cook, covered, until spinach wilts, about 2 minutes. Let cool; squeeze out excess liquid. Stir in ham and a pinch of thyme. Cut a long, thin pocket into each chicken breast. Stuff spinach mixture into pockets, then press the edges of chicken together and seal closed with toothpicks. In same skillet, heat oil. Add chicken and brown on each side, turning once or twice. Add wine, salt and remaining thyme; reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, until chicken is cooked through, about 10 minutes. Serve topped with pan juices. Serves 4.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream and put in 9 x 13 baking dish. Prepare the stuffing per recipe on the box. Spread over the top of the chicken. Sprinkle poppy seeds over the top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk and put into a large bowl.
Cool a little.
Add 4 cups of flour, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add yeast mix.
Beat well.
Add about 3 more cups of flour and cooking oil.

title: grandma ellen's fruit salad
directions: *Fresh fruit of any kind can be substituted for the canned fruit.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil cabbage.
Saute meat with onion.
Add oregano, parsley, garlic powder, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Blend cottage cheese and egg until smooth.
Alternate layers of meat, Mozzarella strips, cabbage leaves and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender at high speed for 1 minute. Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350°.
If glass plate is used, bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Keep in closed oven for additional 5 minutes.

title: bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients gently, but well.
Place in bean pot and bake at 300°, uncovered, 5 to 6 hours (cover last hour) or cook in slow cooker overnight on low heat.
Serves about 8.

title: vegetable platter combinations
directions: Put cauliflower in the center of platter.
Put small whole beets on the outside with green beans and carrot sticks.
Mound baby carrots surrounded by green peas and onions.
Mound broccoli surrounded by yellow row of squash.

title: uncle joe's famous chili
directions: Saute chopped
onions in oil.
Add garlic, hot jalapeno pepper, salt and pepper and tomato puree.
Cook one hour.
Add ground chuck,
vinegar
and chili powder;
cook one hour.
Add hot dogs, mild jalapenos and kidney beans; cook one hour.
Add Velveeta and hot
sauce;
cook
1/2 hour.
Add cut up onion on top.
Simmer and serve hot hot!!!

title: scrambled eggs pie
directions: Mix cereal and margarine; reserve 1/4 cup.
Spread remaining cereal mixture in ungreased pie plate or quiche dish (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Heat 1/4 cup margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until melted.
Beat eggs, milk, chives, seasoned salt and pepper with hand beater.
Pour egg mixture into skillet; add bacon. Cook over low heat, stirring gently, just until eggs are almost set.
Quickly spoon into pie plate.
Arrange cheese, overlapping slightly, around edge of plate.
Sprinkle with reserved cereal mixture.
Heat, uncovered, in 375° oven until cheese is melted and eggs are firm, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 320 calories per serving.

title: nana's molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the margarine, egg and sugar until creamy.
Add molasses.
Add all other ingredients; mix until well blended.
Refrigerate dough for 6 to 8 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Pinch off cookie dough and roll into balls, then roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet a few inches apart.
Press down with fork; bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk until wet. Put on floured board and knead lightly.
Divide into three pieces. Roll each piece (not too thin).
Spread apples on dough and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up and pinch ends. Cut in 2-inch pieces.
Place in pan. Sprinkle lightly with sugar.

title: black cherry jello dish
directions: Mix together Jell-O, boiling water and crushed pineapple.
Let congeal.
Spread remaining ingredients on top of Jell-O.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, milk and shortening. Beat with a fork; do not overbeat.
Add canned corn.
Pour half into greased cast-iron heavy frypan.
Add seasoned meat, onion and peppers.
Add rest of cornmeal batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Cut peaches into pieces and sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over them and set aside.
Mix flour and sugar together, then add milk.
Mix well.
Place flour mixture in 13 x 9-inch dish that has melted margarine in it.
Then gently place peaches evenly over mixture, then spooning sugary syrup over this also bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir with spoon.
Spread in pie shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Form into balls about 1 1/2-inch diameter.
Place remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add meatballs to tomato mixture.
Cover with lid.
Continue cooking for 2 to 3 minutes or until boiling. After boiling, cook for another 20 minutes.

title: oven meatballs in stroganoff sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine milk, onion, eggs and salt. Add bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add meat and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 dozen small balls, 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 48 meatballs.
Contains 222 calories per 6 meatballs.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts; stir occasionally.
Add spaghetti, ham, parsley and pimiento; heat. Makes about 4 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms, celery and green pepper in butter.
Add chicken, Veg-All and soups.
Put pie crust in deep pie dish.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Cover with second pie crust and prick with fork.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled clam mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Remove and finely chop mushroom stems; set aside.
Brush mushroom caps with melted margarine.
In medium skillet, cook garlic in 2 tbsp. margarine until tender. Stir in flour.
Add chopped mushroom stems and remaining ingredients except mushroom caps, mix well. Mound into mushroom caps. Place in shallow baking pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fricasseed chicken
directions: Dress and cut chicken as for frying. Wash, then salt and roll in flour. Fry until light brown. Remove to roaster. Add 2 cups hot milk or water. Cover and let cook 2 to 3 hours. Cook until tender. Serve with mushrooms, if desired.

title: cheese pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat 1/2 of the pineapple juice, sugar and flour until thick.
Put pineapple in buttered casserole and mix in cheese.
Pour heated mixture over pineapple and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in 2 qt. saucepan.
Add rice.
Saute until golden brown.
Add onion, cilantro, garlic powder and chicken broth.
Stir well.
Stir in tomato paste and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Cover & reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients together and shape in a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit and cereal brunch cake
directions: Mix cereal and juice; let stand until soft.
Add oil, egg and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: calamaria and rice(greek)
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the olive oil.
Add the squid and a small amount of water (1/2 cup) and the tomato sauce. Simmer for approximately 10 minutes.

Add 2 to 3 cans of water (using tomato sauce can). Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. When the squid feels soft and tender to the touch, add the rice, white Worcestershire sauce, oregano and bay leaves. Cook thoroughly at low heat until the rice is soft.
Preparation time:
15 minutes. Total cooking time:
45 minutes.

title: t-shirt stain remover
directions: Mom told me that after Grandpa K died, Grandma wanted to stay on the farm alone.
So they set up a plan.
At a certain time, once in the morning and once in the afternoon, Mom would call Grandma on the phone.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients together and drain off excess grease.
Mix the remaining 9 ingredients together.
Add to the meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: eggs in a basket
directions: In a medium bowl add water to croutons.
Stir to moisten. Press crouton mixture into buttered 12-inch pizza pan.
Break eggs around crust.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until eggs are set. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top. Return to oven until melted (about 2 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp and wild rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cooked macaroni, cheese and eggs in a bowl and then pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in milk.
Put butter over the top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until the top noodles become lightly brown.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Cut crust off fresh sliced white bread.
Spread bread with mayonnaise.
Place an asparagus spear (medium size, canned) on edge of bread and roll up.
Place roll in piece of waxed paper and twist ends.
Place all the rolls in pan and place in refrigerator overnight with damp towel on top to keep from drying out.
When ready to serve, take off waxed paper and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: baked beans
directions: In a Dutch
oven, add water and beans.
Bring to a boil and simmer
hours.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Combine salt, brown sugar,
mustard,
molasses,
catsup,
pepper and ground celery. Mix well
and add to beans.
Add rest of the ingredients and bake at
for
2 to 3 hours.
Add more reserved liquid, if needed.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the Bisquick, milk and margarine.
Put the can of mixed vegetables into the bottom of casserole dish, then the soup over the vegetables, then the chicken over top of the soup.
Pour the Bisquick mixture over top and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: meat balls
directions: Grate onion and garlic; add to meat.
Add rest and shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute on low: peppers and onions until tender.
Remove from oil, then use same pan to brown chicken strips.
Add garlic and salt to taste.
Place onion and peppers back into skillet.
Add soy sauce, teriyaki sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer it all on low for 20 minutes.
Heat tortillas.

title: strawberry-filled cake roll
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Beat egg yolks in mixing bowl until thick and lemon colored, using electric mixer at high speed.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar. Blend in vanilla.
Beat egg whites in another bowl until frothy, using electric mixer at high speed.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff, glossy peaks form.

title: toffee pudding surprise(makes 6 servings)
directions: Place in each of 6 serving dishes, 1 marshmallow.
Set aside. Cook according to package directions the pudding mix.
Pour hot pudding over marshmallows in serving dishes.
Cool, then chill. Place in a saucepan the chocolate morsels and water.
Place over low heat and stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Spread over top of chilled pudding in serving dishes.
Chill.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place chicken in a flat baking pan.
Top with cheese.
Mix sour cream, soup and sherry; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with butter and water and place on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill pickles
directions: Select thin cucumbers, wash and dry.
Dissolve 1 cup salt in 4 quarts water; add cucumbers and let stand 12 hours.
All cucumbers must be under brine.
It may be necessary to prepare more brine. Drain and wipe dry.
Place in sterilized jars with layers of horseradish and dill.
Combine remaining 2 quarts water and 1/2 cup salt and vinegar; heat to boiling and pour over cucumbers. Partly seal.
When fermentation stops, pour over enough fresh cooled brine containing vinegar to cover; seal.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: date nut balls
directions: Put margarine, sugar and dates in pot on stove over low heat until dates are mushy.
Set off to cool, then add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well and roll into balls
in powdered sugar.

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: Add 1 tablespoon of salt to 4 quarts of boiling water; gradually add shells.
Boil, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Drain out portion of water, allowing shells to remain in warm water in large bowl.

title: barbecue
directions: Saute onions and hamburger.
Simmer all together for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Drain pineapple and add juice only to jello and water.
Put in refrigerator until slightly thick. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together, then add jello.
Mix in pineapple and cherries; pour into mold.
Keep refrigerated.

title: avocado and shrimp salad(lenten salad)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add avocado and shrimp.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce, topping with mayonnaise.

title: saucepot meat balls and spaghetti(this is quick, easy and surprisingly good!)
directions: Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mash all lumps.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Save whites in another bowl.
Stir or mix until eggs are well blended.
Add water.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: manicotti(serve 8)
directions: Brown meat and garlic; drain fat.
Blend the next 5 ingredients.
Stir in meat.
Fill manicotti shells.
Cover with marinara sauce.
Add about 2/3 can of water.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° in a covered dish.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix 2 eggs, oleo and cake mix together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and 1 box powdered sugar, minus 1/2 cup, together.
Pour on top of mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup powdered sugar on top.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Measure sugar and syrup into 1-quart saucepan and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and peanut butter and finely cream.
Continue stirring to obtain a velvety smooth consistency.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Make 1 cup. Good over ice cream.

title: ceylonese beef
directions: In a large heavy pan, cook onions in oil over moderate heat, stirring until golden.
In a bowl, combine 3 tablespoons vinegar, salt, pepper and beef.
Add this to the onions and cook over moderate heat until beef is browned, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cumin, turmeric, garlic and bay leaves.
Stir for 30 seconds.

title: egg substitute deviled eggs* * * * *
directions: These recipes are fairly new and
have been taken from magazines.
The cake I found after I made a chocolate mousse with raspberry sauce and already had the raspberry liquor.
We must have been living in Texas at the time.

title: creole chicken jambalaya(serves 8)
directions: In large saucepot or Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add onions, green onions and peppers.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Add chicken and brown on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Add ham, sausage, tomatoes, tomato paste and salt.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Add water and cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Stir frequently.
Add additional water if rice begins to stick to bottom of pan.
Before serving, stir in Tabasco sauce.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and milk together.
Add snow and eat.
Enjoy!

title: chili cheese square
directions: Sprinkle chilies and cheese in bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Combine baking mix, cream, eggs and salt in a medium size bowl; beat until blended.
Pour over chili cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with olives.

title: mouse knuckles
directions: Soften margarine. Add vanilla and sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Shape into balls.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Roll twice in confectioners sugar.

title: greek pasta and beef
directions: In a skillet cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile in bowl combine macaroni, egg and Parmesan cheese. In a greased 3 quart baking dish spread half of macaroni mixture. Top with beef mixture and remaining macaroni mixture. Pour sauce over top. Bake uncovered at 350 for 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly and heated through. Let stand five minutes before serving. Yields 12 servings.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter. Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth. Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar and peanut butter until it is a coarse, crumbled mixture; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until fluffy.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch; beat into egg yolks. Beat in hot milk gradually.
Cook in a double boiler until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cover bottom of pie shell with 2/3 of the peanut butter mixture.
Pour in the hot custard.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans with cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Add mushrooms and Cheddar cheese.
Add 1/2 can of onion rings.
Place in casserole dish and cook at 325° for 35 minutes.
Remove and place remaining French fried onion rings on top.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: easy doughnuts and holes
directions: In frying pan or pot, heat oil.
Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic storage bag or something similar in size.
Separate biscuits.
Take shot glass to cut out holes.
Carefully add raw doughnuts and holes (a couple at a time) to oil and cook, turning once until light golden brown.
Remove and let cool to room temperature or slightly above and place into bag of sugar mixture. Shake and serve.

title: tom thumb's chicken souffle(serves 12)
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 8 slices of bread. Saute the mushrooms in the margarine; remove from the heat and combine with the olives, eggs, onions, mayonnaise, parsley, salt and pepper. Spread this mixture over the bread in the baking dish and place the remaining bread on top. Mix the soup and sour cream together and pour over the top of the bread. Refrigerate overnight. Remove from the refrigerator and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm but not dry. Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cut cranberries in half.
Mix with sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Add marshmallows, pecans and grapes.
Whip 1/2 cup whipping cream and fold in mixture.

title: curried lentils with chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except peas, in large soup pot. Simmer for 40 minutes.
Serve with polenta or brown rice and prepared curry sauce.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Stir eggs, vanilla, sugars, milk, water, and lard.
Add 6-8 c. all-purpose flour.
Dissolve yeast pkg. in 1/2 c. warm water and 1 Tbsp. sugar.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Knead together and let rise.
After risen, roll out
and spread butter, cinnamon, and sugar (brown or white). Roll up and slice desired amount of cinnamon rolls.
Let rolls rise again.
Put 1 stick of melted butter and 1 c. sugar into a baking pan.
Place rolls into pan. Cook for 25-30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with glaze.
Dough will stay good in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: ham-macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
Add ham, cheese, pickle relish, peas, onions and dressing.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Chill.

title: tell your neighbor cake
directions: Empty cake mix, flour and instant pudding into bowl.
Add eggs, water and oil.
Blend well.
Beat for 4 minutes until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine spinach, seasonings, Parmesan cheese and sour cream. Place in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.

title: corned beef in beer
directions: In crock-pot, place potatoes, onions and carrots.
Trim excess fat from brisket.
Place meat atop vegetables.
Pour beer over all.
Finish filling crock-pot with water.
Cover; cook on low heat for 9 to 11 hours.
Slice brisket thinly across grain.
Serve with vegetables.

title: peanut butter balls(buckeyes)
directions: In top of double boiler, place semi-sweet chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Melt until smooth and dip balls.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate until set.
Makes 60.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Cook peas.
Drain water.
Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve cold.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on crust.

title: special fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
In a large bowl, combine chocolate chips, margarine and Marshmallow Creme; set aside.
In a large, heavy saucepan, combine the sugar and evaporated milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°), 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour mixture in slow stream into chocolate chip mixture. Stir constantly until chocolate is completely melted and fudge loses its gloss.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in prepared pan and cool for several hours.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Spread into 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan or 2 (7 x 11-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mother ginger stack cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Melt butter in saucepan. Pour melted butter into a 13 x 8-inch glass baking dish. Spread graham cracker crumbs evenly along the bottom of the dish. Then add coconut to form next layer. After the coconut, add each ingredient separately. Each one forms a layer. Pour the condensed milk evenly over the entire mixture. Bake at 325° about 25 minutes or until golden brown. Let cookies cool completely. Cut into squares.

title: egg and sausage bake(breakfast dish)
directions: Separate and press crescent roll dough in 13 x 9-inch pan. Pinch edges together to seal.
Cut cooked sausages into bite-sized pieces and layer on top.
Shred Mozzarella over sausage and mix eggs with milk, green pepper, salt and oregano and pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° until eggs set and crust is golden brown.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Bring all ingredients, except cabbage, to a boil.
Taste for flavor.
Add cabbage. Cover pot and simmer at least 45 minutes.

title: caramel nut crispies
directions: Melt caramels until smooth.
Add nuts and coconut; mix together.
Add cereal; toss together until mixed well.
Put in greased pan.
Spoon out tablespoonfuls.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered casserole dish. Combine the dry ingredients in a separate bowl. Cut in butter. Mixture will get crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: california salad
directions: Just before serving, combine all ingredients, except Fritos. Add Fritos last.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Can sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 12 minutes in 375° oven.

title: lemon souffle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Mix in pudding.
Cool and fold in egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into serving dishes.
Refrigerate.

title: swedish meatball stew
directions: Cook meatballs in onion soup mix according to soup directions about 30 minutes.
May add potatoes, cut small or any other vegetable.
Or may serve over noodles.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Cook onion, celery and pepper in oil until done.
Drain and add corned beef, flaked, and barbecue sauce.
Cook on simmer until it begins to get dry like barbecue, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
Use more sauce if you want.
Don't put corned beef in refrigerator; flake with fork.

title: grandma gladys' baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: foolproof fresh apple cake
directions: Add together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add the two together.
Mix in 3 cups fresh diced apple and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with 8 slices of loaf cake.
Top with strawberries, then Cool Whip.

title: tuna salad
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor.
Process until smooth.
May serve on bun with lettuce, pickles, pepper and onion; or tuna on bun, only.

title: dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Scoop into balls.
Bake until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: cinnamon nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Grease and flour 2 square pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs in mixing bowl. Beat 5 minutes, high speed on mixer or by hand until well mixed. Blend flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add alternately in 3 additions with milk, starting and ending with dry ingredients. Beat on low speed just until smooth; fold in nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Browned Butter Icing.

title: pound cake(diabetic)
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
Grease the bottom and about 1 inch up the side of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat butter at medium speed of electric mixer until creamed and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 6 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, eggs one at a time, beating about 1 minute each.
Scrape bowl frequently. Mix flour, salt and nutmeg.
Gradually add dry ingredients to egg mixture and beat until thoroughly blended.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Add vegetable oil and cocoa. Gradually add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the coffee. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spider candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler.
Stir in peanuts and noodles until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and allow to harden.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Make a day ahead and chill in refrigerator.
Serve with corn chips.

title: different baked irish potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes to clean.
Make 4 or 5 slices almost through each potato.
Fill slices with Butter Buds and Mrs. Dash.
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour half of mixture into 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except crackers.
Put crackers in a baggie and pour ingredients over crackers.
Shake well.
Let stand 1 hour and put in clean baggie.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar.
Blend in egg and cooled shortening.
Gradually blend in salt and flour.
Knead and place in buttered bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Form into rolls or bread.
Place in buttered pans and butter tops.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add melted butter and rest of ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top will be crunchy but good.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cut bread in narrow strips.
Brush with melted butter.
Roll in grated cheese.
Bake in slow oven.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg, water and cinnamon in a bowl.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Place in a skillet in preheated canola oil.
(Preheat the oil over medium heat.)
Cook until egg is done or light brown. Top with fresh fruit or enjoy plain.

title: bear roast
directions: Preheat roaster oven to 325°.
Place roast on a rack and salt and pepper.
Place 2 bay leaves on top of roast and then the onion. Add water.
Make a foil tent over roast and put cover on.
Bake 3 to 4 hours, until tender.
Check periodically to make sure it's not dry.
Add water if necessary.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil one minute; remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil one minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Add coconut.
Pour immediately into baked pie shell.
Finish with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Let cool at room temperature.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook deep pie shells. Drain Veg-All; mix with cream of chicken soup. Add chicken breast. Add a little broth or water to moisten so mixture will not be so dry. Then put the mixture in deep pie shells. Turn small pie shells upside down on top of mixture. Bake at 350° until pie shell is brown and mixture is hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Make sauce of margarine, flour and milk and add 1/2 of the cheese.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix macaroni and sauce.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put flour in bowl (4 cups). Pour in all ingredients and mix.
Add approximately 3/4 cup of flour as you knead the dough until it stops sticking to your fingers.
Roll into two balls.
Put thin layer of oil over the dough balls.
Cover the dough and place in refrigerator until cold.
Roll dough out on pizza pan.
(Shaking some corn meal on the pan prevents the dough from sticking.)

title: spiced punch
directions: Pour all juices into crock-pot (8 cup capacity).
Simmer. Serve hot.
Great at Christmastime.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together and add lemon rind.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; mix 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice and pour over hot bread.
Cool 15 minutes before removing.

title: yankee corn
directions: Open and pour corn into casserole dish.
Crush the crackers and add to corn.
Add egg; mix well.
Pour butter over corn.
Bake until brown, at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Arrange cut chicken pieces in a baking dish.
Combine butter, honey, mustard, salt and pepper and spread over chicken pieces. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste frequently with pan drippings.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to directions.
Set aside.
Marinate boneless chicken breasts in milk, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Saute onions, mushrooms and celery in butter until onions are transparent.
Stir into wild rice along with cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and top with marinated chicken.
Cook until chicken is done.

title: grandma's penuche
directions: Stir sugar, cream and syrup together.
Microwave 7 minutes then stir; microwave for 8 more minutes.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add nuts and turn onto greased pans.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook peeled and cubed potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain well and cool slightly.
Cook bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towel and crumble.
Mash eggs.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine the first three ingredients, stirring well.
Combine the next four (dry ingredients) in a large bowl.
Add the first three combined ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix well, then add the last four ingredients and again mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chicken salsa
directions: Mix salsa, sugar and mustard.
Pour over chicken; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna apple salad
directions: Mix tuna and other ingredients together.
Contains 100 calories per half cup.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in 2-quart saucepan and bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: biscuits from herman
directions: Mix Herman with flour to which has been added soda, salt and oleo or oil.
Add more flour if too thin, making a stiff dough. Lightly knead to form biscuits and drop in buttered pan.
Allow to rise double in size.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for a few minutes; reduce heat and bake about 25 minutes.
This mixture can be made into bread instead of biscuits.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir egg yolks into sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add small amount of milk, stir until smooth then add the rest.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stir until thick.
Remove from fire.
Add oleo and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: sunday punch
directions: Heat water with sugar until dissolved.
Cool, then add to pineapple and orange concentrate. Put the lemon juice and banana in blender and puree, then add to the juice mixture.
Freeze until ready to use.
Add
cold Spritz when ready to serve.

title: green onion appetizer bites
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Shape into small ball over end of each green onion.
Dip or roll end of onion in seed or nuts or paprika. Chill.
Makes about 20 appetizers.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Serves 10.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together until they form a peak.

title: candied pecans
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream in a large skillet.
Bring to a boil and boil
for	3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add pecans and stir quickly to coat.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: spicy grilled pork chops
directions: Have barbecue grill ready!
In large plastic Ziploc bag, place all seasonings; mix together well.
Place 2 chops at one time into bag with seasonings; shake well (continue until all chops are seasoned).
Place on grill; cook for 15 minutes.
Turn over and cook 20 minutes or until done.
(With pork, cook until completely done.)

title: london broil
directions: Trim fat; place London broil in a glass dish.
Mix all the rest in a small dish, then marinate in refrigerator over steak for 6 hours or you can do it overnight, this will make it tender.
You can then cook on the grill or broil 5 to 10 minutes on each side. Slice thin and serve.

title: root beer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix in 12-cup Bundt cake pan as directed on package, except substitute root beer for the 1 1/4 cups water and add root beer concentrate with the root beer.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack or heatproof serving plate; remove pan.
Cool cake completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve with ice cream sprinkled with candies.

title: fresh veggie bars
directions: In food processor or hand shredder, shred the first 4 ingredients together.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing; mix until smooth.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat green beans, drain and pour into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over green beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: one pan curly-roni
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, brown ground beef. Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and seasonings; bring to a boil. Add curly-roni and return to a boil. Cover and cook on low 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Stir in Parmesan cheese and simmer, uncovered, until thickened.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and boil until sugar dissolves.
When cool, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate to marinate at least 8 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 3/4 inch slices.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in skillet then saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms.
In same skillet brown meat.
Reserve 2/3 cup broth, stir in remaining broth, onion, catsup and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend remaining broth with flour; stir into meat.
Add mushrooms; heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Cook noodles as directed.

title: pepperoni pizza rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Unroll French Loaf on cookie sheet. Brush bread with olive oil and then spread pizza sauce, leaving about a 1/2 inch edge around bread. Place pepperoni slices and then top with shredded cheese. Begin rolling bread lengthwise and pinch seam and edges.
Brush with olive oil and sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake seam side down for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool slightly and then cut in 1 1/2 inch slices with a serrated knife. Makes a great party favorite.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Chop onion and saute until soft in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except for ribs, and simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.
Divide ribs for serving and place in shallow pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Brush every half hour with the sauce and turn.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dessert ring coffee cake
directions: Thoroughly cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together salt, baking powder and flour and fold into creamed mixture.
Mix together last four ingredients.
Spoon half of the batter into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with half of nut mixture.
Top with remaining batter and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 20 minutes in pan before removing.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese immediately.

title: mystery salad
directions: Heat tomatoes to boiling, add jello and stir until dissolved. Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into 4-cup mold or 8 individual molds. Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold and serve topped with a dollop of dairy sour cream mayonaise, if desired.
8 servings. This is very good.

title: poor man's "crab" cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and oil.
Shape into patties.
Roll in flour and saute in oil until brown.
Serves 6.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
(Plan ahead, since this takes about 2 months.)
Add enough gravy to cover.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add 1 quart water. Cook until done.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Sift the flour with the powder and salt. Cut in the shortening until well cut up. Add milk and hand stir.
Turn out on floured counter.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut biscuit shape. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Combine curry, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Rub seasonings into chicken and set aside.
In a skillet, combine orange juice, rice, water, brown sugar and remaining salt.
Mix well.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hoggies
directions: Chop up ham or Spam. Chop onions and cheese.
Put into hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and bake until hot.

title: sour milk fried cakes
directions: Beat eggs until thick, add sugar and melted shortening.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Refrigerate.

title: chili
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add chili mix and stir.
Combine all ingredients in large pot; heat to a boil.
That easy!

title: molasses pie
directions: Mix egg and flour together until smooth.
Add milk and maple syrup.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Combine sifted cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in the flavorings.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour
and 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato puffs.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with potato puffs.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: sausage-apple-sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet. Remove meat to a casserole dish and saute onion in same pan.
Put onion and apple atop sausage and cover with sauerkraut and caraway seed.
Make mashed potatoes according to package directions. Spread over sauerkraut and garnish with cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marcel's hoagie salad
directions: In large bowl, slice lettuce and tomatoes, then add sliced turkey, ham, salami, cheese and onions.
Add peppers and Italian dressing; toss.
Serve immediately or lettuce will become soggy!

title: fillets in lemon butter
directions: Arrange fish in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a 1-quart casserole, place butter and cook 1 to 2 minutes until melted.
Blend in parsley and lemon juice and pour over fish.
Top with crumbs, then sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Real good.

title: coconut pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine all ingredients; stir until moistened.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts; place on cookie sheet, about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until light golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: stacy's scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Wash potatoes. Pare thinly and remove eyes. Cut potatoes into thin slices to measure about 4 cups. In greased 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes in 4 layers, sprinkling each of the first 3 layers with 1 tablespoon onion, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and dotting each with 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle top with remaining onion. Salt and pepper and dot with remaining butter. Heat milk just to scalding. Pour over potatoes. Cover. Bake 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 60 to 70 minutes longer until potatoes are tender. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: peachy ginger coffee cake
directions: About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Drain peaches well.
Pat dry with paper towels and arrange in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over peaches.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt in a bowl.
With a fork, mix in molasses, water, salad oil and egg until blended.
Pour batter over peaches and bake for 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool cakes in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
With knife, loosen cake and invert onto a plate.

title: beefy mac 'n corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain.
Stir in soup, spaghetti sauce, water and cooked macaroni.
Heat through.
Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: rye bread dill dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Hollow out one loaf of round rye bread.
Cut the removed rye bread into small pieces for dipping.
Put dip into the hollow loaf shortly before serving.
The round rye bread may be purchased at Schnucks.

title: quick and delicious potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 1 quart casserole dish after sprinkling with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Sweet potatoes should be cooked and mashed.
Combine them with sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add last three ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Cook until thick, then add coconut.
Pour into cooled baked pie crust.

title: creamed peas
directions: Heat peas and margarine until boiling.
In a cup, combine flour and sugar; mix well.
Add to boiling peas.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Serve immediately.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Slice onions.
Cook until almost done.	Butter a baking pan. Layer onions with bread crumbs, salt, and pepper.
Pour white sauce over onions and crumbs.
Repeat layering until pan is full ending with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat.
Add whipping cream that has been whipped.
Fold in pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in Jell-O dissolved in 1 cup hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: rev. traylor's  favorite rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix well and let stand while you make up the pastry shell. Bake for 40 minutes at 425°.
Take from oven and put meringue on (egg whites well beaten with 2 tablespoons white sugar); return to oven for about 10 minutes or until topping is well browned.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Garnish with shredded carrots.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: alex's favorite cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet or pat in pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for drop cookies, and longer for a pan cookie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion, drain well.
Mix celery soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, egg, cheese, garlic, salt, pepper and almonds. Add well drained broccoli and onion.
Place mixture in a greased 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese crackers on top and return to the oven for an additional 7 to 10 minutes.

title: paella
directions: Clean clams by soaking in warm salty water for 15 minutes. Rinse and repeat.
Scrub shells in clear water.
Set aside.
Boil water and wine; add 3 cups rice and simmer until done, 35 to 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil in a large frying pan or wok. Add chicken parts and onions; brown well on all sides.
Add garlic, tomatoes, salt, pepper, paprika, cayenne and Tabasco.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Slowly add cooked rice to simmering mixture.
Simmer for an additional 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add olives, peas, parsley, prawns and scallops.
Stir gently.
Place clams on top. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until clam shells open. Remove and discard any clam shells which do not open.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sours
directions: Brown meat; add water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Do not boil. Combine green pepper, onions and pineapple chunks, reserving syrup. Set aside.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Add all other ingredients to meat.
Cook until thickened.
Add pineapple, onion and pepper.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar; pour over rest of ingredients.
Salt to taste.

title: low-fat vegetable pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables and rolls and set aside.
Place rolls on cookie sheet to form crust.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
Top with dressing mix. More or less Italian dressing may be used to make spreadable consistency.
Place vegetables (raw) on top.
May use carrots, radishes, celery, etc., according to your taste.
Chill until ready to serve.
tags: low-fat dry creamy Italian dressing mix

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in pan.
Add instant chocolate. Stir mixture and bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Beat mixture until it starts to cool and thicken.
Place by teaspoonfuls onto buttered cookie sheet to cool.
Coconut can be added.

title: sherry's marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.
Stir well. Pour over meat and cover.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours or several days (more flavor the longer it sits).

title: nut crescents
directions: Mix together yeast and sour cream.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in softened oleo and mix in flour using hands.
Form dough in 7 patties.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight. Roll dough in confectioners sugar 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 16 wedges.
Put nuts in wide end and roll like crescents.

title: jeanne's pasta and peppers
directions: In large frying pan, place dry pasta, the pepperoni, seeded pepperoncini peppers, then drained red peppers, then rosemary. Place pan on preheated burner and pour 3 cups boiling water over. Cover and boil 10 minutes.
Add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Stir and heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in top of double boiler. Stir in egg yolk and milk.
Add margarine.
Bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook until margarine is melted, stirring constantly.
Gradually add vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and smooth.
Cool completely.
Combine apples, pineapple and pecans.
Stir dressing into fruit. Refrigerate just until chilled.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place boiled and deboned chicken breasts in a casserole dish. Mix the soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers.
Mix the poppy seed with crackers and put over chicken dish.
Dribble oleo over top of crackers.
Bake in moderate oven for about 20 minutes, until it bubbles good.
Eat warm or cold.

title: delicious pistachio bread
directions: Mix all together.
Grease 2 bread pans.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 2 pans.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon on top.
Put rest of batter in pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all together to make a dough.
Drop by teaspoon onto a nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over melted butter in a 10-inch heavy skillet.
Arrange pineapple over brown sugar.
Use cherries too, if desired.

title: chicken filled shells
directions: Mix together chicken, peas and carrots, Miracle Whip and onion. Stuff cooked shells and arrange in baking dish.
Combine soup and water and pour over stuffed shells.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.	Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.	Cool cake layers before icing.

title: spicy fried cabbage
directions: Stir-fry all ingredients in a large skillet with oil.
Season with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
You may need more than 1 can Ro-Tel, depending on size of cabbage.
Cook until cabbage is lightly browned.
If you like it more spicy, add a little cayenne pepper.

title: fried apple burritos
directions: Warm tortillas over stove burner or in microwave oven for easy rolling.
Place about 2 tablespoons apple filling near center of each tortilla.
Fold back flap over filling.
Fold in sides and roll, sealing filling well to prevent oil splatters.
Heat oil about 1 inch deep to 360°.
Fry apple burritos with flap ends underneath.
Hold down with tongs a few seconds to fry evenly. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer: Crush pretzels, medium or fine. Melt oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar. Mix together. Pack into long baking dish. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Cool.

title: best cookies ever
directions: Mix altogether.
Make 1-inch balls out of the dough and place them on a cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Boil lasagna until soft but firm.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix syrup and lard thoroughly.
Sift soda, ginger and flour together and add to syrup and lard mixture slowly.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in oven, heated to 375°.

title: family reunion buns
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm. Add sugar, salt and melted butter. Add yeast and warm water until yeast dissolves. Add beaten egg and work in flour. Let rise double in bulk (1 hour). Then divide dough in half. Cut each half into 12 equal parts and form into balls. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Brush with butter and let rise (1 hour). Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Saute hamburger and onion together.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and warm.
Serve with Doritos.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk. Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well. Add yeast and beaten egg. Blend thoroughly. Add remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled in bulk.

title: crab dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then place in mixing bowl, beat until soft.
Add Miracle Whip and fold until light and fluffy.
Add onion and crab meat.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: diet applesauce coffee cake
directions: Combine first
ingredients
in
bowl
and set aside. Sift together flour, baking
powder,
salt, soda and dry milk. Combine remaining ingredients in
large
mixer bowl and beat 3 minutes. Blend in
dry
ingredients	and
one half applesauce ingredients. Pour one half
mixture
into
x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Dot
with one half of remaining applesauce mixture.
Pour over
remaining
batter and then dot with last half of
applesauce mixture.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes until
golden brown.
After
removing
from
oven, sprinkle cake with 6 packets of Equal.

title: boiled cake #2
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients 3 to 5 minutes; cool.
Add molasses. Sift dry ingredients; add to cooled mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Put in 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything (except corn flake crumbs and butter) together and put in baking dish.
Mix corn flake crumbs and butter together.
Put over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage until done.
Drain grease.
Add potatoes, cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, cocoa and margarine. Stir well.
Add eggs and beat with electric mixer for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add salt, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans, if desired. Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: special mai-tai
directions: Shake well with cracked ice and strain into large old fashioned glass, about 1/2 full of crushed ice.
Decorate with maraschino cherry speared to wedge of fresh pineapple.

title: stephen's mexican casserole
directions: Fry ground beef; drain.
Layer in pan, chips, meat and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crazy cinnamon rolls
directions: Beat cottage cheese and margarine until creamy.
Add flour and let stand in refrigerator overnight or at least 3 hours.
Divide dough into 2 parts and roll, one at a time, in a circle about 1/4 inch thick.
Melt some margarine and cover over dough.
Sprinkle with a combination of cinnamon and sugar.
Cut in 1 1/4-inch wedges and roll up, starting at the outside circle.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: campfire stew casserole
directions: Spray bottom of baking pan with Pam.
Then press in meat in a thin layer.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put slices of butter on top.
Peel and slice onions, potatoes and carrots 1/4-inch thick. Layer on top of meat:
onion, potato, carrot.
Season again to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ortega chili and tortilla casserole
directions: Butter oblong casserole dish and layer tortillas, chilies, cheese and olives until gone.
(Use 2 tortillas between cheese and chilies.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cocoa, flour, butter, milk and vanilla.
Pour into blender and mix for about 1 minute. Cook mixture in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: honey grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients until it becomes a smooth liquid.
May need to heat the honey in microwave if it is too thick.
Let chicken soak in sauce for 30 minutes. Cook on grill and baste remaining sauce on chicken.

title: quick peach melba
directions: Place 1 peach half in a dessert dish. Spoon about 1 teaspoon jelly into each peach.
Pour milk into small mixing bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat at low speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour at once over peaches.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then chill.
Makes 5 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a casserole dish. Cover. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: cheddar port dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together about 40 seconds and chill. Serve with crackers, etc.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Chop and mix
crab
sticks with cheese.
Add chives and serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Mash
artichoke;
stir
in bread crumbs, cheese, garlic powder and
salad
dressing.
Roll into balls, using one teaspoon per ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: zippy meat balls
directions: Combine beef, oatmeal, milk, 2 of the onions and salt.
Form into balls. Roll in flour and brown. Put into casserole. Combine catsup, vinegar, water, sugar and other onion.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy skewered shrimp
directions: Whisk together olive oil, turmeric, pepper, garlic, basil, mint, red pepper and vinegar.
Rinse shrimp; pat dry with paper towels.
Toss shrimp in marinade to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight, tossing occasionally.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before barbecuing.
Preheat grill.
Remove shrimp from marinade (reserve marinade).
Grill shrimp in a seafood basket until pink (3 to 5 minutes) turning 3 or 4 times with marinade.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place thick cut of round steak on piece of foil.
On top, place 1 can of tomatoes or 2 large tomatoes, sliced.
Add all other ingredients on top of meat.
Wrap foil around meat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Toss together with other ingredients; chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli shrimp alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute the shrimp and garlic in butter until shrimp turn pink. Remove and keep warm. In a skillet, combine the cream cheese, milk and parmesan cheese; cook until cheese are melted and smooth. Place broccoli in a saucepan with 1 inch of water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 6-8 minutes or until tender. Drain. Stir broccoli, shrimp, salt and pepper into cheese sauce; heat through. Drain fettuccine and top with shrimp mixture.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on bag; drain.
In casserole dish, add broccoli, can of mushroom soup, can of chicken soup and jar of Cheez Whiz and blend together well.
Add cooked rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add a couple of Kraft singles on top before baking, if desired.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add enough water to make a paste, then add the remaining water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir.
Pour at once into jars.
When cold, place in refrigerator. Makes 2 cups syrup.
May be used as a topping for desserts or in making chocolate flavored drinks.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place one piece of chicken, boned-side up, between two pieces of clear plastic wrap.
Working from the center to the edges, pound lightly with a meat mallet to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove plastic wrap.
Repeat with remaining chicken breast halves.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put all ingredients in skillet.
Simmer until thick.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: dill cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth. Refrigerate one hour.
Serve with fresh, raw veggies.

title: angel delight
directions: With serrated knife, cut angel food cake crosswise into 4 layers.
Place bottom layer on cake plate.
Cover with sliced strawberries.
Place second layer on top and cover with sliced bananas.
Place third layer on bananas and cover with sliced kiwi. Frost entire cake with lite Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: grilled potato skewers
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat potatoes and enough water to cover to boiling point.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
When potatoes are cool, put onto skewers.
Preheat broiler or grill.
In a small cup combine oil, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Place skewers on rack or in broiling pan or grill.
Brush with mixture and cook 6 to 8 minutes, occasionally brushing with mixture and turning.

title: jo's baked squash
directions: Place squash, onion, salt
and	pepper	in baking dish. Cover with soup undiluted.
Bake at
for 1 hour or until squash and onion are
tender.
Cover
with
cheese
and
bake another 10 minutes.
Can cover with cracker crumbs.

title: portuguese cabbage soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef with garlic, pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley. Makes about 3 quarts.
Soup can be frozen.

title: cheesecake creme dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Stir in rind and ginger.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups.

title: singapore vegetable curry with gluten or chicken
directions: Cut all vegetables in big chunks, including onion.
Boil 3 to 4 cups water in deep pan, enough to cover vegetables, together.
Drop vegetables according to which cooks the longest, including beans and onion.
Add 1/2 can coconut milk when vegetables are half done. Add curry powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes and put off fire.
Add the rest of coconut milk.
Add fried gluten and egg chunks before serving.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar together. Chill overnight.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Melt paraffin and chips in double boiler.
Insert toothpicks in dough balls and dip halfway up ball in chocolate mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: lemonade or limeade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, melted lemonade or limeade and milk.
Pour into crusts. Makes 2 pies.

title: angel's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt chocolate in microwave as per package instructions.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Coat with chocolate and let sit until solid.
Great!

title: chipped beef
directions: In small frypan, combine soup and milk over low heat.
Add beef and heat to serving temperature, stirring constantly.
Serve over toast or hot noodles.

title: christmas cloud pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add fruit cocktail.
Pour into cooled pie shell.

title: "night before" egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: after hours?
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade concentrate with the Southern Comfort.
Add champagne and 7-Up right before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Crumble ground beef in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook until just done and then drain well and set aside.
In same pan, cook onions and green peppers slightly.
Add meat, olives, garlic, tomato sauce, water, eggs, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer while preparing noodles and cheeses.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash apples. Slice into very thin pieces.
Arrange apples in greased, square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: pot de creme
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar, egg and vanilla in an electric blender.
Heat milk, in a small saucepan, over moderate-low heat, until boiling.
Pour into blender; cover and blend on high for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into small serving dishes.
Chill for 3 hours or until firm.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy in double boiler.
Cool in large bowl.
Mix the melted candy and Cool Whip by hand.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: five layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip evenly on a 12-inch round tray.
Mix avocados and lemon juice and spread over bean dip.
Blend sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning and spread over avocados.
Sprinkle tomatoes and green onions over sour cream mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and garnish with sliced black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Bring to boil; cook for 5 minutes, then can and seal.

title: nut drop cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla to mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 2 minutes.
Blend in Wesson oil, unsweetened chocolate or powdered cocoa and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Mix well.
Bake in oiled 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Mix all but chops; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over chops; refrigerate for several hours.
Baste and barbecue.
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic-flavored green beans
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook whole beans in salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In a 12-inch skillet cook beans and garlic in hot butter about 7 minutes or until crisp-tender, tossing constantly.
Add parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: tasty crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Break up uncooked beef and put in crock-pot.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and then the remaining ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Thicken with solution of 2 tablespoons cornstarch dissolved in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir in solution, cover and cook until sauce is thickened.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, raw veggies or chips.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease baking dish and cover bottom with bread crumbs.
Lay oysters on crumbs.
Season and cover with more crumbs.
Pour milk and oyster liquid over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake in hot oven at 425° about 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together butter, egg and sour cream.
Stir in corn.
Add dry corn bread mix; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: basil broccoli
directions: Chop broccoli, including tender part of stems, into 3/4-inch pieces.
Arrange in a 9-inch glass pie plate with the florets in the middle and the stems around the edge.
Sprinkle on stock or water.
