Cover with vented plastic wrap; microwave on full power until tender, about 5 minutes.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Serve with Leek and Sweet Pepper Toss or Sesame Carrot Sauce.
Serves 4.

title: spinach strawberry salad
directions: Blend oil, sugar, salt, pepper, dry mustard and wine vinegar in small bowl and set aside.

title: party punch
directions: Boil water and sugar until mixture is clear.
Add gelatin and stir.
Add remaining ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir well. Freeze to a slush.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: overnight sweet rolls
directions: In Bundt pan, put all ingredients in the order given.
Cover pan.
Let set on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: scorched scotchies
directions: Melt almond bark in a glass bowl in microwave until slightly "scorched."
Turn bowl and check every 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mound 1 tablespoon of candy mix on waxed paper for each Scotchy.
Cool.
Store in airtight container in a cool place.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients into the hot gelatin.
It makes a different and delicious fruit salad.

title: low sat-fat chex snak mix
directions: Mix all cereals, pretzels, and nuts together in large bowl. In small bowl or in measuring cup, mix remaining ingredients well. Pour liquid mix over cereal mix and toss to coat cereals well. Place in microwave on 80% power for 4 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Microwave on 100% power for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Let cool. If you are using wheat or bran Chex, wait until last 2 minutes to add these.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Fill a 2 quart baking dish alternately with sliced potatoes, cabbage and celery.
When filled about an inch from top, place lump of butter on top, season with salt and pepper.
Pour milk over until about 2 inches from the top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: honey jelly
directions: Clean
small
jars
as if for canning. Stir honey, corn syrup, water
and	lemon
juice in a large saucepan.
Bring to hard boil over
medium-high
heat.
Add pectin. As soon as it comes to rolling boil that can't be stirred down, time exactly 1 minute and
remove
from heat. Skim off any film.	Pour hot jelly	in hot
jars. Leave 1/8-inch headspace. Screw on lids. Cool on
wire rack. Check for good seal.	Store in dark place up to 1 year.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix marshmallows with fruit, alternating so the marshmallows will not stick together.
Combine all ingredients together, making sure all is moistened well with the cream.
Press into a buttered pan and chill for at least 24 hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Combine oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until combined.
Stir in carrots and nuts. Pour into 2 greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole mix the ham and mushrooms.
In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour the egg mixture evenly over the ham.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until egg is almost set, pushing cooked egg to the center of bowl several times during cooking.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine all ingredients and place in roaster. Place cut up chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: green pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water.
Combine vegetables and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing and mustard.
Pour over salad.
Toss gently.
Chill.
Serves 4.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and add onion and garlic; saute over low heat until onion is tender.
Sprinkle flour over and cook for 3 minutes.

title: zucchini on the half shell
directions: Trim ends of zucchini; cut squash in half lengthwise.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add grated onion and bouillon cube; crush cube.
Add zucchini, cut side down and cook until golden brown.
Turn; add water and cook, covered, over low heat, about 10 minutes or until tender.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Sprinkle toasted, chopped pecans in pie shell. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix Dream Whip and milk. Combine cream cheese mixture and Dream Whip mixture. Pour into pie shell. Pour blueberry pie mix over cream mixture. Chill before serving.

title: green coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Grease Bundt cake pan.
Coat bottom and sides of pan with sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Pour half batter in pan; sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and walnuts. Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, sugar and beer.
Pour in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese-broccoli stuffed pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water for 15 minutes or until done. Rinse with cold water.
Drain well and set aside.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Chop finely and set aside.

title: old-fashioned beef stew(from 1975 edition)
directions: Roll pieces of meat (which has been cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes) into mixed flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in fat or oil. Add chopped onion and brown.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture over meat and brown.
Add enough water (hot) to cover.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add vegetables but not peas.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Then add peas until tender, if frozen about 10 minutes.
Add chopped parsley and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: claudine's king ranch chicken
directions: Combine condensed soups, broth and tomatoes.
Set aside.
Oil a 3-quart casserole.
Layer half of tortillas, half of chicken, half of onion and bell pepper and half of cheese in casserole. Pour half the soup mixture over layers.
Repeat layers and pour remaining soup mixture over top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: To make the salad dressing, mix first 7 ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine the rest of ingredients and simmer all until tender.
Pour into jars and seal hot.
Makes approximately 8 quarts.

title: layered taco dip salad
directions: Layer first the 2 cans of bean dip and jalapeno dip.
Add the jalapeno dip to your desired consistency.
Second layer, mix the sour cream and taco seasoning; spread over your first layer.

Then spread the nacho and taco shredded cheese over the second layer. Chop green onions and spread on third layer, then the tomato. Then, if desired, salsa and peppers may be added or placed on the side.

title: dell's salad
directions: Put the drained, crushed pineapple into a 3-quart bowl.
Add the Jell-O powder and stir until dissolved. Add the cottage cheese and stir well. Add the Cool Whip and stir well.

title: homemade butter
directions: Soften oleo.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Mix with electric mixer until fluffy.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and beat well.

title: linda's goulash(quick 'n easy)
directions: Cook meat and onions in a large frying pan (drain if necessary).
Add tomato soup.
Pull tomatoes into small pieces and add with juice to pan.
Add macaroni and pepper; simmer 15 minutes.
Add pork and beans; simmer an additional 15 minutes. After beans are added, mixture will thicken.
Serves about 6.

title: kona crab squares
directions: 1. Heat oven to 375°.
2. Unroll dough in four rectangles. Place in a 15 X 10 X 1
inch jelly roll pan. Press unto bottom and halfway
up sides of pan to form crust. Press perforations to
seal.
3. Bake 10 minutes.
4. Mix salad dressing, juice, and pepper until well
blended.
5. Add cheese, crabmeat, green onion, and parsley and mix
lightly.
6. Spread mixture over crust. Continue baking 12 to 15
minutes or until cheese is melted. Let stand 5 minutes
then cut into squares. Makes 24.

title: chocolate chip nut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, margarine and vanilla; blend well. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: caramel candy
directions: Bring to rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Slowly add another cup of cream or milk and cook until hard ball stage.
Pour in pan.

title: iced tea punch
directions: Bring to boil 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water.
Add other ingredients, except strawberry soda and food coloring.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over ice ring in punch bowl.

title: baked applesauce
directions: Place apples in a 1-qt. baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. In a small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and vanilla; mix well. Sprinkle over apples. Cover and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until apples are tender. Uncover and mash with fork. Serve warm.

title: favorite fried mozzarella
directions: Slice cheese into sticks 1/2-inch thick; coat with flour.
Dip in eggs and oil and crumbs to coat.
Arrange on wax paper lined plate.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Fry in 2-inch deep oil at 380° until golden brown.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and carrots and cook until macaroni is tender, 2 minutes longer. Rinse under cold water to cool; drain.

title: mama mae's sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Generously butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Vigorously
beat
eggs
and sugar together in large bowl.
Stir
in all remaining ingredients except whipped cream.
Pour
into	prepared
casserole
dish and bake 1 hour, until barely firm.	Serve tepid, garnished with whipped cream.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix the margarine, granulated sugar and flour together until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Pack into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Add the Cool Whip.
Spread on top of baked mixture.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken with onion salt and lemon pepper.
Prepare rice.
In medium skillet over medium heat, cook chicken in butter about 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove to platter and keep warm.

title: tuna herb casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
Melt butter; saute onion. Stir in soup.
Gradually blend in water; stir in herbs and tuna. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup cheese.
Add macaroni.
Put into a casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: ambrosia fruit compote
directions: Grate 1/2 teaspoon orange peel; set aside.
Section oranges, reserving juice.
Halve and pit plums.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Combine fruits and orange juice.
Heat pineapple syrup, brown sugar and orange peel until sugar dissolves.
Stir in rum flavoring.
Pour over fruits.
Stir; chill.
Garnish with coconut.
Serves 8.

title: my favorite pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, spices and salt.
Gradually add evaporated milk.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Spread into large, shallow baking dish.
Mix flour, margarine and milk; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy apricot punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Add crushed ice before serving.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Fry bacon slices until crisp. Drain and crumble. Set aside. Place onions in skillet. Brown slightly. Add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook for 20 minutes, covered. Add onion mixture to beans. Add crumbled bacon.
Pour into crock-pot and cook on low for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef, until hot.
Add beef.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In a 1 quart microwave-safe casserole dish, stir together pork and beans, molasses, onion, mustard and ginger.
Cook covered on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through, stirring once. Sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Break the egg in a 1-cup measure; beat.
Finish filling cup with milk.
Mix the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and Crisco. Add liquid.
Handle lightly.
Pat out on floured board.
Cut; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets and save 1/2 cup of beet juice. Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; heat to boiling. Add sliced cooked beets and simmer 10 minutes. Pack beets into a jar and pour syrup over the beets. Store in refrigerator.

title: eggnog
directions: Chill liquids before mixing.
Separate egg whites and yolks. Beat yolks.
Add sugar.
Stir in whipped cream, milk and cream. Beat egg whites and fold in.
Dust with nutmeg.
Chill.
Makes 10 servings.

title: prunella cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add
sugar
and
melted shortening and beat again.
Add well chopped prunes.
Add milk and sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in layers for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Drain apples, reserving liquid.
Place apples into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour 1 1/8 cups reserved liquid over top.
In a bowl, sift remaining 1 cup sugar with flour.
Thoroughly mix in the melted oleo.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown on top.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Mix like pie dough crust until crumbly.
Put on large cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Watch and stir often until light brown.
Remove from oven and put 2/3 of this in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Put pudding on top of crust, then Cool Whip.
Put rest of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except peanut butter.
Add peanut butter,
chocolate
chips,
oatmeal, M&M's and pecans. Drop on greased sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Place a small amount of chicken at the wide end of each roll and roll them up.
Seal and place seam side down in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thoroughly combine the soup and milk; pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; let cool.
Sift flour with soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat at high speed on electric mixer the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla for about 3 minutes, until light and smooth.
At low speed, beat in chocolate. Beat in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat in water until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost as desired.

title: fresh hot pepper tomato dip
directions: Mix all together and season to your own taste with salt, black pepper and garlic powder.

title: shrimp aspic salad
directions: In small container, mix gelatin with small amount V-8 juice and heat in boiling water.
When completely dissolved, mix with remaining juice.
Stir well.
Add bell pepper, onion, celery, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces, garlic salt, salt and shrimp; mix well.
Add milk to cream cheese until smooth.
Pour into molds. Pour V-8 mixture over cream cheese; chill.
Fills 20 molds.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Form into balls (small).
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and roll in sifted powdered sugar.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix crumbs, nuts, sugar and cocoa; add combined syrup and rum. Using 1 tablespoon for each, shape into balls.
Roll balls in additional powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Approximate yield:
2 dozen.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add beef and cheese together in crock-pot until cheese melts.
Add salsa.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add flour, bananas and pecans.
Spoon batter into greased loaf pan.

title: petite party cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling point in saucepan.
Mix in flour at once.
Stir constantly until mixture leaves side of pan and forms into a ball, about 1 minute.
Beat eggs one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Whip mixture until velvety.
Drop by level teaspoonful in small mound on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot 400° oven about 20 minutes. Cool puffs and split to fill with chicken salad or your favorite sandwich filling.
Yields about 40.

title: quickie chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Arrange in greased casserole dish.
Put chicken on top.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Cook about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pickled eggs
directions: You will need a gallon jar.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a cupcake pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers and onions with salt.
Place ice on top and water; refrigerate for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Drain cucumber mixture.
Place in jars and cover with liquid mixture.
Seal and bathe 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 pints.

title: deer stew
directions: Place meat in crock-pot and cover with water.
Dice vegetables and add to meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, buttermilk and mashed bananas and beat.
Stir in dry ingredients and vanilla. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole or microproof container.
Sprinkle with water; cover with plastic wrap and pierce plastic wrap.
Microwave on High power for 8 to 9 minutes or until cauliflower is tender-crisp.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, add 2 tablespoons of the sugar. Combine shortening, salt and remaining sugar.
Add water not used to dissolve yeast.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board and knead until dough is spongy and does not stick to hands.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until doubled in size.
Work down and work into buns and place them in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 large buns.

title: crisp cabbage 'n bacon
directions: Coarsely chop the cabbage.
About 15 minutes before serving, in large skillet, cook bacon slices until crisp, 6 to 8 minutes. Remove from skillet.
Pour off bacon fat.
Return 2 tablespoons to skillet.
Add cabbage, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once.
Crumble bacon over cabbage. Serve.

title: beef - o - matic juice
directions: Combine; chill.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Contains 9 calories/4 ounces.

title: oatmeal brunch cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; mix well.
Add oil.
In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Add to oatmeal.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients; combining well.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still hot, spread with topping.

title: almond brittle
directions: In a saucepan, cook the first 3 ingredients until almonds begin to crack, stirring constantly.
This takes about 20 minutes. Will turn caramel color.
With a teaspoon, drop a few drops in a cup of cold water to test for hard crack.
When hard, a ball or strand forms in a cup of water.
Pour mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Set aside.

title: golfer's chicken
directions: Combine dry soup, dressing and jam.
Mix well until smooth. Wash chicken and pat dry.
Slightly overlap in flat, buttered baking dish.
Spoon 1 or 2 tablespoons on each piece and spread over all.
Bake at 225° for 4 or 5 hours or however long your golf game takes.
Be careful to put well below your heating element if using electric oven.

title: cheese balls(2 balls)
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts and/or parsley.
Chill.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt cheeses and margarine over hot water, fold in egg whites. Coat well each cube of bread and freeze on cookie sheet.
As needed, bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandma lucy's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes at 350°.
Broil a few minutes to crisp bacon.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mama's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Fold in creamed mixture. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter or margarine in oven.
Roll chicken in margarine.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and bake for 30 minutes.
In 12-inch skillet over low heat, bring 1-inch of water to boiling.
Add broccoli and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and bring to boiling.
Cover and cook 1 minute; drain.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in skillet (one that can be put into oven).
Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk; roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in skillet and brown slightly on both sides, on top of stove, then bake in oven for 30 minutes. Mix soup and 1 cup of buttermilk.
Pour over chicken.
Return to oven and bake until tender.

title: mexican quiche(appetizer)
directions: Place chilies on bottom of a greased 10-inch pie/quiche pan. Scatter cheese evenly over chilies.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over cheese.
Pat top to moisten all cheese.
Bake at 400° to light brown, about 20 minutes. Serve with plain tostados.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In 1 tablespoon oil, fry hamburg and drain.
Combine beef and all ingredients except carrots and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour. Add carrots for 10 minutes. Add potato for 20 minutes.
The carrots need 1/2 hour, the potato needs only 20 minutes. At the end of cooling, add 6 or more ounces of tomato juice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Cut chicken in 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces and pound lightly between
pieces
of
waxed paper.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour and
fry
in
hot
oil
on both sides. Finish all of the chicken
pieces
and drain oil.
Add the remaining ingredients and let it reduce over high heat until it is nicely thickened. Serve with lemon slices and parsley for garnish. Serves 3.

title: strawberry freeze salad
directions: Soften ice cream.
Fold pineapple, whipped topping, cherries, cream cheese and banana into ice cream.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Freeze until firm, at least 3 hours. Makes 15 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil rice in 1 cup water for 20 minutes. Boil and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Dot with the margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese begins to bubble.

title: crescent italian zucchini pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and shredded cheese.
Stir in zucchini mixture.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Press over bottom and sides to form crust.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add salt and flour.
Add broth and stir.
Mix the other stuff and pour in pie shell and put top on pie.
Put slits in top.
Bake at 425° to 450° approximately 30 minutes.
Keep checking.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with bottom pastry; flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp salad(reke salat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on open-faced sandwiches.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, milk, pumpkin, cornstarch and pumpkin pie spice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook until a small amount dropped into cold water forms a soft ball, 238° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: dewberry delight
directions: For the crust,
mix 1 1/4 cups flour, 1 stick of butter and 1 cup pecans.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to
15 minutes.
Cool.
Cook berries, water, 1/2 cup flour or less and sugar.
Mix
cream cheese and eggs.
Mix and pour over cool crust.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Pour berries and pat small carton of Cool Whip on berries, refrigerate.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook onions in 3 tablespoons butter until wilted, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add broth, rice and broccoli and cover.
Simmer over low heat until tender, 10 to 20 minutes.
Puree soup; add cream and reheat.
May serve with grated Parmesan cheese on top or chopped dill and butter.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese fingers
directions: Slice bread crosswise into 1-inch fingers, leaving attached. Mix cream cheese and salad dressing mix together; spread on bread. Pile on toppings.
Broil until brown and bubbly.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen fingers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients, then mix in sour cream.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: salmon sandwiches
directions: Drain liquid from salmon and break into small pieces.
Add onion, celery and Miracle Whip and blend.
Add salt and pepper and pickle relish.
If desired, white tuna can be used instead of salmon.

title: cheese log
directions: Grind cheese, garlic and pecans in finest grinder.
Mix well. Add vinegar and salt to taste.
This mixture is rather soft.
Form into small log and put in refrigerator.
When cheese is cooled, mix together paprika and chili powder and roll log in mixture. Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: irish potato croquettes
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Add to potatoes while still beating.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot cooking oil in skillet.
Allow to brown on 1 side then turn and brown the other side.

title: one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: blue cheese pears
directions: Let cheeses come to a room temperature.
Combine softened cheeses, walnuts and garlic in a large mixer bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer until mixture is smooth.
If necessary add a few teaspoons milk to mix.
Form cheese mixture into a pear shape. Place cinnamon stick in top as a stem.
Add mint leaves at the stem.
Pat paprika on sides of the pear to create a shadow.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with desired crackers and fruit. Serves eight.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions 1/8-inch thick.
Melt butter and saute onions slowly for 1 1/2 hours in a large soup pot.
Add all other ingredients, except bouillon, salt and wine.
Saute over low heat 10 more minutes.
Add bouillon and wine and simmer for 2 hours. Adjust color to a rich brown with caramel coloring or browning sauce.
Season to taste with salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yield: 2 quarts soup.

title: garden relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, peppers, onions and carrots. Use plastic or stoneware and let set all night with a handful of salt sprinkled on top.
Drain off the next morning.

title: pear pie with candies crust
directions: Fill well-greased pie pan, 9-inch size, with thin slices of pears.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon, if desired, together. Work the butter into dry ingredients with a pastry blender or with 2 knives until the mixture is like coarse corn meal.
Pat mixture on top of pears.
This forms the top crust of the pie.
There is no bottom.
Bake.
When cool, serve as a regular pie with plain cream or whipped cream.
Delicious with a scoopful of ice cream on each piece.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb slush
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and water for 30 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Strain
through a colander.
Discard pulp.
To liquid, add lemonade and jello.
Freeze.
Serve with ginger ale, lemonade or 7-Up.

title: creamy shell soup
directions: Simmer water, chicken, diced onions, celery, minced parsley, bay leaf, salt and pepper in Dutch oven until chicken is tender. Remove bay leaf; discard.
Remove chicken, cool.
Skin and debone, set aside.
Add potatoes, green onions, bouillon cubes, seasoned salt and poultry seasoning to broth.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk, macaroni and chicken, return to simmer.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Add flour, stirring constantly, until
mixture begins to brown.
Add to soup, blend well.
Let soup stand 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Season to taste.
Garnish with nutmeg and chopped parsley.

title: antipasto
directions: Seed and wash peppers; cut into strips.
Place in bowl (not metal).
Boil vinegar and water.
Pour over peppers.
Cover with Saran Wrap and leave on counter overnight.
The next day, rinse peppers thoroughly with cold water.
Mix peppers with artichokes, olives, mushrooms and roasted peppers.
Add olive oil and oregano to taste.
Place on platter with slices of salami and cheese.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Can substitute with one pound of canned sweet potatoes.

title: caramel date fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over low heat.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, caramel chips, vanilla, dates and nuts. Stir 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain, rinse with cold water and drain thoroughly again.
Combine rotini, cucumber, Feta cheese, olives and onions.
Blend together the oil, vinegar, parsley, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over rotini and toss gently to blend.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with tomato wedges before serving.
Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine all ingredients until spreadable. Spread on both sides of loaf.
Put loaf together and wrap in foil.
Heat in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Stir dry ingredients into pie pan.
Add milk and oil.
Stir flour with fork until completely dampened.

title: pork chop cranberry casserole
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let stand 30 minutes.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Toss cranberries, onion, celery, stuffing and evaporated milk.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Brown chops on both sides.
Place on top of stuffing mix.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudgeroos
directions: Mix chocolate chips and butter and melt over hot, boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift together and gradually stir in 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oats.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato bake
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup drippings.
Gradually blend broth into flour until smooth; slowly stir into drippings.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch), arrange potatoes; pour broth mixture over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with bacon.

title: fudge
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine marshmallow, sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Nestle's bits until melted and smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.

title: no sugar added mandarin orange pie
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and reserve liquid.
To reserved liquid add enough water to make 1 cup and bring to a boil.
Mix with the sugar free orange jello until dissolved.
Refrigerate until thick and fold in the cool whip until smooth.
Layer in the graham cracker crust 1/3 of the orange mixture, layer of orange slices, rest of jello mixture and top with remaining orange slices. Refrigerate 4 hours until firm.

title: butterscotch pies
directions: Make two 8-inch pie crusts.
Bake until done.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise together.
Add water and mix.
Sift flour, soda and cocoa.
Add vanilla last.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add bananas and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to banana mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with any type fresh fruit.

title: hot crab salad
directions: Chop green pepper, onion and celery fine.
Combine crab and shrimp; add to vegetables.
Blend with other ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk in large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat for 1 to 2 minutes (with whisk or lowest speed on electric mixer) until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in the whipped topping and half the crushed cookies.

Place 1 tablespoon of remaining crushed cookies into each of 8 to 10 (7-ounce) paper or plastic cups. Fill the cups about 3/4 full with the pudding mixture, then top with the remaining crushed cookies.
Decorate with gummy worms, etc.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy chocolate candy
directions: *May substitute cashews with 1 cup unsalted peanuts and 1 cup raisins or a 12-ounce bag of coconut.

title: beef kabobs oriental appetizers
directions: Cover cubes of meat with a well blended mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Set in refrigerator at least 4 hours, turning meat several times.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Have margarine
and eggs at room temperature.
Use only cake flour.
Mix ingredeints.
Bake
at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Don't turn oven on until ready to put cake in.

title: western stew
directions: Pour dressing over meat; cover and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade.
In Dutch oven, brown meat over low heat.
Add marinade and 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue to simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add remaining water to flour, stirring until well blended. Gradually add flour mixture to hot meat and vegetables, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Simmer 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broken taco shell casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of broken shells in lightly buttered dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain; add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer 10 minutes; add tomato sauce.
Spoon over shells.
Add 1 cup cheese, then rest of broken shells and rest of cheese.
Top with tomato, sliced.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lois' sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: old-fashioned chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Cool and cut in strips. Melt butter and flour.
Blend well.
Add chicken stock and milk. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add diced potatoes, eggs and chicken.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with pie crust.
Cut slits in dough.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: deer steak and onions
directions: Soak steaks in vinegar and water for 1 hour.
Wash and sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Roll in flour.
Place in skillet with hot grease.
Brown both sides on high.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cut up onions in slices and place over steaks.
Add a pat of butter to each steak.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until done, turning once.
Worcestershire sauce may be sprinkled over steaks while cooking to add more flavor.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine and mix well ingredients, except potato chips and almonds.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan; cover with crushed potato chips and slivered almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: "i can't make a pie crust" english apple pie
directions: In medium-size bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and the water until smooth and thick.
Stir in pecans.
Mound apples in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix granulated sugar with remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Spoon pecan topping over apples in dollops.
Bake on lowest rack in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
(Apples should be tender when pierced.) Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Reheats great in microwave.

title: feathery chocolate layer cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder and salt and sift three times.
Cream shortening thoroughly; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Add flavorings.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate (375°) oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread chocolate frosting between layers and over cake.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave oleo to melt at High 30 to 45 seconds.
Add brown sugar and milk; microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla. Gradually stir in sugar and peanut butter.
Press into buttered pan.
Cool; cut into desired pieces.

title: hot fruit souffle
directions: In a small saucepan, combine fruit with water; cover and cook until fruit is very soft.
Put fruit and liquid in blender container and process; transfer to small bowl.
Beat yolks lightly and add to fruit in bowl with lemon juice.
Beat whites until stiff and fold them into the first mixture.
Transfer to 2 individual souffle dishes and bake at 350° until tops are brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve at once.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: sauce vinaigrette sans egal
directions: Gather all the oils, wine and spices.
Separate the egg.
In a blender, put the egg yolk, mustard, wine, wine vinegar and spices. Mix these well at medium speed about 1/2 minute, being careful not to turn the blender off.
While running, slowly add the oil, pour in a thin stream into the liquid in the blender.
Be careful so oil won't separate.
Refrigerate and serve cold on salad. Makes 4 cups.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Step 1:
Make a salt brine strong enough to float an egg.
Add cucumbers; let stand 2 1/2 weeks.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into 2-inch squares when cool.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: You will need round toothpicks (they are stronger).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked 9-inch pie crust with mixture.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, vanilla and cooking oil in large bowl; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first ingredients.
Mix well.
Add apples and pecans; mix well. Place batter in greased and floured Bundt pan and cook for 1 hour at 300°.

title: tater dogs
directions: Peel and cut in half several potatoes.
I usually do about 8. Brown on all sides in skillet of hot oil.
Place in a casserole dish and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Add a stick of margarine cut in patties and cover.
Bake in 350 oven until done.

title: date nut bars
directions: Add flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar to large mixing bowl.
Mix on low speed until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Mix melted butter, eggs, nuts and dates together and then add to dry ingredients. Make certain all ingredients are completely mixed.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until dark brown. Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars when cool.
Coat bars with powdered sugar.
Yields 42 bars.

title: popcorn balls
directions: *Add a few drops of food coloring to mixture or use colored popcorn.

title: mini-quiche
directions: Flatten each biscuit.
Spray large muffin tins with vegetable spray.
Press biscuits into tins.
Combine remaining ingredients. Spoon into biscuit shells.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick chocolate pudding
directions: Combine first four ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cheese just before serving.
Add dressing of choice.

title: chicken pot roast
directions: Cut up vegetables; place chicken in large Dutch oven.
Dump soup over chicken; add 1/2 can water.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add cut vegetables; cook until vegetables and chicken are tender, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can cook in crock-pot on high about 4 hours.
(I don't cook chicken before adding vegetables.)

title: tomato corn salad(10 minutes to the table)
directions: Place corn and a small amount of water in a microwave safe bowl. Cover and microwave on high for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until corn is crisp-tender; drain.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter, gradually adding sugar. Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and wax until dissolved.
Use a toothpick to dip each ball into chocolate mixture until almost completely covered.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in frying pan.
Add soup, sauce, salt, sugar and garlic salt.
Cook slowly.
Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onion in casserole. Place layer of noodles, then meat and cream cheese.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Do not crush corn flakes.
Mix all ingredients well in a large mixing bowl or a dishpan.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes for soft cookies or 10 to 12 minutes for crunchy.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Cut dates and raisins and sprinkle with baking soda.
Pour boiling water over this mixture and allow to cool for 10 minutes. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Add date mixture, flour and nuts.
Bake in 4 greased cans (the size of 15 ounce Hunt's tomato sauce).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: doritos pizza
directions: Fry hamburger meat and chopped onions. Drain. Add Ranch Style beans. Layer Doritos on cookie sheet or pizza pan. Pour hamburger mixture over Doritos evenly. Mix Ro-Tel and soup in pan. Pour over meat mixture. Then sprinkle olives, green chilies and cheese. (Optional: Green olives, etc.) Bake at 375° approximately 20 minutes until melted.

title: joey's favorite cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat in skillet and drain. Add cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes, stirring frequently. Combine Alabama football. Serve with Fritos Scoops or tortilla chips.

title: croatian donuts(prikle)
directions: Dissolve yeast with warm water; add 1/2 cup flour and set aside to rise.
Add yeast mixture to other ingredients; mix all together and let rise.
Mixture will be moist.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil and fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
May add sugar for appearance and extra sweetness.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together, blending until all ingredients are mixed.
Line muffin tins with paper liners or spray tins with Pam.
Spoon mixture into muffin tins, filling about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 48 miniature muffins or 18 to 20 regular size.

title: aunt hattie's butter cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and beat well.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Keep cool.
Roll very thin using only 1 panful at a time, so dough will stay cold.
Bake at 350°.

title: old fashioned mincemeat
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Cool and grind.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 hours. Cool and use for pie and/or store in freezer.

title: california pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain, and rinse in cold water.
Place in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: barbecue sauce for pork
directions: Combine vinegar, margarine, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, chili powder, paprika, black pepper, salt, mustard, catsup, red pepper and water in 6-quart saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Will keep for several months. Yield:
128 servings.

title: microwave peas supreme
directions: In 1-quart casserole, microcook butter at High for 1 minute. Stir in onion; microcook at High for 1 minute.
Add peas, mushrooms and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Cover and microcook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Garnish with tomato halves.

title: beer pancakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the packaged biscuit mix, sugar, ground cinnamon and ground nutmeg.
Stir together the beaten eggs, beer and cooking oil.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Add a little additional beer if thinner pancakes are desired.

title: broccoli-rice casserole ii
directions: Combine broccoli
with
onion and cook as directed.
Drain. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
After cake has cooled, split layers in half (makes 4 layers).

title: chicken pepperoni
directions: Saute until lightly browned the ham, olive oil and pepperoni. Add and cook slowly until half done the chicken.
Place mixture in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer slowly for several hours until chicken is 2/3 done.
Stock can be completed ahead of time.
When cold, cover and refrigerate.
Bring mixture to a boil before proceeding.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Put everything in a crock-pot.
When the cheese is melted, it is ready to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix in flour and sugar.
Pat in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
In medium bowl, mix beef, sausage, onions, crumbs, chilies, parsley, eggs, chili powder and garlic. Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until browned.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Put apples in pie shell.
Mix dry ingredients and pour over apples.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Dissolve coffee in 2 tablespoons water in saucepan. Melt Hershey bars in coffee mixture over low heat. Cool 10 to 15 minutes. Fold Cool Whip/rum mixture into chocolate. Pour in pie crust and refrigerate. Before serving, dollop edge with Cool Whip and sprinkle toasted almonds and grated chocolate on top of pie, if desired.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the orange slices, in large saucepan.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour or longer.
Do not boil. Strain before serving.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: lite ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple and orange segments.
Save 5 tablespoons of pineapple juice.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Add 1 egg yolk. Heat on stove until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool. Combine drained pineapple, oranges, bananas, cherries, marshmallows and nuts.
Add thickened pineapple juice and stir. Add sour cream and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8 people. Serve as a dessert in fruit dishes or as a salad on lettuce leaf.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Layer onions, Parmesan cheese and cracker crumbs.
Microwave 10 minutes at 60% power.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift salt, spices and flour; add alternately with milk. Add coconut, nuts and prunes and raisins.
Pour into tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Bring everything to a boil.
Bake ribs at 500° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or use 1 tablespoon instant coffee in 1/2 cup water.

title: fluffy orange salad
directions: Beat together cream cheese and cheese spread.
Drain and cut up peaches, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Beat reserved syrup into cheese.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Whip the cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and blend.
Add milk and boil hard for one minute.
Add confectioners sugar gradually.
Beat mixture as you add sugar until it loses its glaze.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Then add Ragu sauce and simmer.
Have noodles cooked and drained.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, put 1/2 of the meat mixture, then 1/2 of the noodles.
Put 1/2 of the sour cream over this.
Repeat these 3 layers.
On top of this sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add yeast mixture and milk to mixture.
Cook at once or store in refrigerator.

title: artie's rhubarb-strawberry jam
directions: Put rhubarb in a heavy pan with very little water, sugar and pineapple. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Let boil about 10 minutes or until rhubarb is very soft. Turn off burner and add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Pour in jars and seal immediately.
I like to keep these refrigerated until used.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix strawberries and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
In a mixing bowl mix together flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in margarine until the mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring until combined.
Spray an 8-inch round baking pan with nonstick spray. With lightly floured hands pat dough into the pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes or until golden colored on top.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
While cake is cooling, prepare whipped topping according to directions using the skim milk.
Split shortcake into 2 layers.
Place bottom layer on a serving plate.
Top with half of the strawberries, then add the second layer of shortcake.
Spoon dessert topping and the rest of the strawberries on top of cake.
Other berries can be used instead of strawberries; peaches are good also.
Serves 8 people.

title: freezer box cucumbers
directions: Dissolve your sugar in vinegar with salt and celery seed. Pour over your onion and cucumbers; let set an hour.
Then pack away in the freezer.

title: fuzzy navel slush
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in large container (1 gallon).
Put in freezer.
Stir occasionally while freezing.
When serving, fill glass 3/4 full and add 7-Up or Squirt.
I use 6 ounces of lemon and 18 ounces of orange juice and add a little more sugar (1/4 cup).

title: deluxe party potatoes
directions: Bring water, milk, margarine and salt to a boil.
Add potatoes, cream cheese and sour cream.
Blend well, using low speed on mixer.
Spoon into greased 11 x 7-inch casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: lipton meatballs
directions: Mix the soup mix and evaporated milk; let stand for 5 minutes. Mix in hamburger.
Roll into balls; place in fry pan.
Brown on each side 5 minutes.
Place meatballs in baking dish.
Cover with cream of onion soup or mushroom soup.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done, at 375°.

title: krispy pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice paper thin (use a slice).
Chop onions and peppers.
Combine with cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: miracle whip potatoes
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in a large bowl.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide into greased aluminum packs. Grill 20 to 30 minutes.

title: noodle taco casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic powder with ground round until brown. Add tomato, cream of mushroom soup and package of taco sauce.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put MBT in hot water to dissolve.
Mix with softened cream cheese.
Chop green onion fine and mix with cream cheese mixture and mayonnaise; then use.

title: oriental chicken breasts
directions: Heat oil in skillet at medium heat.
Brown chicken on both sides; pour off excess oil.
Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, ginger and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken; simmer for 35 minutes, covered. Remove chicken from pan.
Blend cornstarch and pineapple juice. Add to skillet with remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, until tender and pepper is cooked.
Serve with rice cooked in chicken broth.

title: smothered steak(crock-pot)
directions: In a crock-pot alternate vegetables and meat.
Start with vegetables first.
Mix tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper together and pour over top of contents.
Cook in crock-pot on low 8 to 10 hours.
Serve on white rice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together.
After it comes to a boil, let boil for 1 minute.
Turn off fire.
Add vinegar and soda quickly; it will become light and foamy.
Pour over popped corn. Now, put into a large cake or roast pan.
Stir to coat evenly. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 250°; stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Store covered.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix sunflower seeds, broccoli tops, grapes and bacon in large bowl.
In
separate
bowl,
mix Miracle Whip, sugar and white wine
vinegar.
Combine
contents of both bowls and mix well.

title: perfection salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and chill.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix and pour in ring mold.
Refrigerate until ready for serving.
A small dish of mayonnaise or other dressing may be put in center.
Garnish with greens, olives and pickles.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass baking dish or deep bowl, combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Turn 2 to 3 times.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Pumpkin Filling:
Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl until well blended.
Spread evenly in bottom of pastry shell.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Chunk up bananas. Blend with other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Place carrots in casserole, stir in croutons & cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients & pour over carrot mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° until brown about, approx. 1/2 hour or so.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delights(cookies)
directions: Measure sugar, cocoa, butter and milk into 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil one minute.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop quickly onto waxed paper in teaspoonful.
Enjoy.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Saute the onion in the margarine.
Add cheese and thawed, drained spinach.
Melt in a double boiler.
Serve hot on rye bread.

title: black bean soup
directions: *Typically found in bags.
Use 1 to 2 bags, depending on amount of soup one is cooking.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan stir well. Add eggs and milk stir until blended. Cook over med heat and stir in vanilla. Let cool 30 mins. Cover custard; chill 8 hrs. Add strawberries, whipping cream, and 3/4 cup sugar to chilled custard. Stir well. Pour mixture into freezer container of 5 qt. electric freezer.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed.
Punch holes in brownies; make instant coffee (as for a beverage) and pour over brownies.
Break candy bars into small pieces.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook pepper, onion and garlic until tender in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Simmer for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients and stir together with broccoli.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ozark honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, honey, soda and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients. Add chicken last.
Mix well.
Put into greased crock-pot.
Cook on high 45 minutes, then cook on low for 4 hours.
Stir twice during cooking.

title: chocolate and cherry ring
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pat into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan or wire rack for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool; sift powdered sugar on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apple.
Let stand overnight in sugar. Dissolve jello in hot water and cool.
Pour over berry mixture. Add pineapple and nuts.
Let stand until firm.

title: iced cocoa
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to water; boil for 15 minutes.
Add milk; chill.
Serve very cold with whipped cream or ice cream as a garnish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add 1/2 of it to pudding.
Save the other half for the top of pudding. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding, making two layers of each.
Top with reserved Cool Whip and sour cream.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Toast bread halves in oven or under broiler and butter.
Mix garlic, cheese, paprika and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread and bake in 450° oven until top is bubbly (about 10 minutes).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender before. Drain off water; add butter, salt, pepper and milk. Mix together, then add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs. Pour in well-greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add ground beef; lightly brown.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, tomatoes and macaroni. Cook for about 30 minutes on medium heat, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add water if necessary.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix the milk, oil and vanilla until smooth and stir into dry mixture.
Mix the last 3 ingredients and sprinkle on top.

title: honey spice bars (finika)
directions: Be sure butter and eggs are at room temperature.

title: springtime pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to package; drain. In large bowl, toss with 1 tablespoon oil, green onions and garlic. In large saucepan, combine broccoli and asparagus with boiling water. Cook 4 minutes. Drain and add to pasta. Add thawed peas, bell pepper, mushrooms, Parmesan and parsley; toss well.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Wash chilies, removing seeds and flattening them out.
Put 1/2 of chilies across the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with all the Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining layer of chilies.
Cover with Monterey Jack cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat yolks with milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour over chilies and cheese in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until lightly browned.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Combine the dry ingredients; set aside.
Stir together eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add them to dry ingredients; mix well.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full (paper lined).
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 400°. Batter may be stored in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Bake up muffins as needed.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: granola snack bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix ingredients together and pat in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on rack, then refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into squares or bars.
Makes 32 bars containing 118 calories each.

title: shut the gate salad
directions: Pour all ingredients into a bowl and with a spoon, stir until well blended.
Ready to serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: On stove melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Cook until it begins to get firm; add pineapple.
Mix cake mix as directed on box; pour over mixture.
Bake for about an hour on 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw package of spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir soup mix, 1 1/2 cups sour cream and mayonnaise together until blended.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts, chopped.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours. Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: mom's cream gravy
directions: Use drippings from the meat that you fry, stir flour in and let brown slightly, add salt and the milk (I use a small can of condensed milk, if you want it richer).
Stir until thick, if you like a thinner gravy, add more milk, if you want a thicker gravy, use less milk.
This recipe has been passed down through several generations.
Goes well with venison.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and return to pot. Add all ingredients, including liquid from the canned vegetables. Cook until rice is done.

title: almond biscotti
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch bars.
Brush top with egg.
Bake at 375° for 16 minutes.
Cut diagonally while warm.

title: linguini with artichoke sauce
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add butter or margarine and melt. Add flour and cook, stirring 3 minutes over medium heat.
Slowly stir in chicken stock.
Increase heat and cook 1 minute.
Add garlic, lemon juice and parsley; cook uncovered over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Recipe can be held at this point for up to 2 hours.
Drain and quarter artichokes.
Add to prepared mixture with cheese and capers.
Cook uncovered, basting artichokes for about 8 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and toss with hot sauce.
Serve with more cheese and chopped parsley.

title: lindsay's ham roll-ups
directions: Must be done night before you serve.

title: orange vanilla french toast
directions: Cut bread into 3/4-inch slices.
Arrange in greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan in single layer.
Beat first 7 ingredients together.
Pour over bread, coating both sides.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
In large skillet, heat oleo; sprinkle bread slices with nutmeg and brown
on both sides.
Serve with syrup or preserves.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: In microwave dish, combine juice, honey, butter, lemon peel, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in cornstarch; mix until well blended. Stir in carrots.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on high 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir once.
Stir, let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: Day Before:
In a small bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, Blend cream cheese until smooth.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes to an hour. Note:
You may use chives instead of onion and add parsley for color. Serve with white sauce and sliced hard boiled eggs.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, sugar, powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Beat zest, juice, oil and water.
Add to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add cranberries and mix.
Pour into greased loaf tin.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn out and cool on rack.

title: strawberry angel food delight cake
directions: Slice cake in half.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and cool whip.
Place layer of icing in between layers of cake with half of fruit.
Finish putting icing on sides and top of cake.
Add last of fruit on top.
Chill overnight and keep refrigerated. Remember to slice carefully with serrated knife when serving.

title: baked ziti and cheese
directions: Parcook ziti according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper, tomato paste, brown sugar, parsley and water for 10 minutes.
Arrange like lasagna, layering ziti sauce and cheeses.
Top with sauce and Provolone cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pear relish
directions: Comb. pears, peppers, and onions. Mix salt and water and pour over mixture. Use enough water to cover. Let stand overnight. Drain and rinse with fresh water. Comb. vinegar, tumeric, sugar and mustard seed in large roaster. Bring to boil for 5 min. Add pears peppers and onions and cook 15-20 min. Put in sterile jars and seal. Yield 8-10 pints

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: banana cake(bake auction)
directions: Mix ingredients, creaming sugar and oleo, then adding eggs and bananas.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 2 layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Delicious with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: peter pumpkin
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take yellow cake mix and sprinkle dry over pumpkin mixture.
Press down into pumpkin.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch together in the saucepan.
Add the water and mix a little more.
Cook over medium heat, stirring all the time. The mixture should start to boil, then thicken. Takes about 5 minutes.
Remove from the stove, cool and pour into plastic or paper cups.
Be careful with food coloring since it can stain, but add a little of it to
each cup and then a drop of detergent.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in stainless steel or glass bowl. Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in chilled cups, mugs or soup plates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crunchy pasta and cheese
directions: You will also need can opener, microwave, 1-quart casserole with lid, potholders, large spoon and large measuring cups.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread in pieces about size of quarter.
Break cheese in bite size pieces.
Arrange ham, bread and cheese in several layers of greased casserole dish.
Pour margarine over mixture.
Beat egg and then add mustard.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Mix together and pour over mixture in casserole dish.
Let stand a minimum of 3 hours, preferably covered, in refrigerator or overnight.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Boil or bake potatoes; peel and mash well.
Mix in butter. Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; add to potatoes.
Add milk.
Dough should be moist, not sticky.

title: smoked ham and lentil soup
directions: Sort lentils.
Rinse well; drain.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, combine all soup ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until lentils are tender but not mushy and meat pulls easily from bone.
Remove and discard bay leaves and lemon peel.
Remove ham shank; cool.
Remove meat from bones; cut into bite-sized pieces.
Add meat to soup.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 (1 1/2-cups) servings.

title: stir-fry
directions: Place oil in very hot skillet or wok.
Add chopped vegetables and stir-fry for a few minutes.
Add rice; stir well.
Sprinkle soy sauce liberally; salt and pepper to taste.
Add meat.
Stir a few minutes longer.
Remove and serve.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding like box instructs.
Mix in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer crackers and pudding, ending with crackers.
Spread frosting over crackers.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Store mix in an airtight container. To serve, place 1 1/2 tablespoons mix in cup, add 1 cup boiling water and stir.
Yield: about 50 servings.

title: radish spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, using a mixer for smooth consistency. Use for a vegetable dip or a spread for crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add cheese, soup, water and broccoli.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (do not cook before freezing).
Can be frozen.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix cornmeal in bowl with egg and oil and mix with milk until batter is of spoonable consistency.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in frypan until hot.
Spoon batter into pan and fry until lightly brown.
If onion is desired, mix the onion with the meal, egg and oil.
Then proceed with recipe.

title: haddock shrimp bake
directions: Place the fish in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread with soup.
Combine butter and seasonings, mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over fish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Grate cheese.
Mix with sausage.
Gradually add Bisquick mix and work into sausage and cheese mix.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter swirl brownies
directions: Combine margarine and brown sugar in a medium bowl; add egg substitute.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until thoroughly combined.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to sugar mixture, stirring well. Divide batter in half.
Stir cocoa into 1 half; stir peanut butter into other half (peanut butter mixture will be thick).
Spoon dollops of each batter alternately into a 9-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut through batters in pan with knife to create a swirled pattern.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven, and let cool completely on wire rack.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: kasutera(japanese pound cake)
directions: Set aside the flour.
Put the first 5 ingredients into a bowl and whip for 7 minutes.
Add flour slowly into mixture and whip for 5 minutes.
Bake in oven at 320° for 35 to 40 minutes (use loaf baking pan).

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and egg. Then add rest of ingredients. Pour in greased and floured cake pan. Cook 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs, beating until well combined.
Add milk, raisins, rice and vanilla flavor.
Pour mixture into greased pan.
Put pan in boiling water.

title: cheesy nachos
directions: Spread tortilla chips over large platter.
In medium saucepan, combine undiluted soup, salsa and 3 tablespoons water.
Heat over low heat to simmering, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 1 minute. Pour soup mixture over chops and sprinkle with scallions and olives.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Mix the eggs, oil and sugar.
Add all the dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Fill each with 1/2 of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix.
Add bananas and mix.
Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Combine dry ingredients with the banana mixture, a little at a time.
Add raisins (boil raisins for a few minutes to soften, cool them, then add to mixture).
Add nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased and floured cookie sheets.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: chicken wiggle(serves 8 with second helping)
directions: Cook hen in salted water until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
There should be at least 1 quart of stock.
Fry onions, celery and pepper in fat from hen.
When tender, add mushrooms, eggs,
pimento, chicken, some almonds and some stock.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Arrange in a large casserole dish a layer of noodles and layer of chicken mixture. Repeat layers until filled and pour stock over all.
Garnish with eggs, olives and almonds.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip or m&m's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly in bowl first 6 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix 2 bowls together thoroughly.
Work in 12 ounce or 16 ounce package of semi-sweet chocolate chips or M&M's.
Drop by rounded teaspoons, 2-inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Dough keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Delicious, but don't beat it as you mix it together.

title: stuffed cabbage(golumki)
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Parboil cabbage and separate leaves using the largest.
Cut ribs off and let cool.
Saute onions with 5 strips of bacon, minced, and a pinch of paprika.
Mix onions and bacon with ground meats.
Thoroughly mix in cooked rice, salt and pepper.
Roll cabbage with 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture in center.
Thoroughly drain sauerkraut and spread on bottom of small roaster.
Take remains of cabbage head and dice and lay on top of sauerkraut.
Place cabbage rolls tightly together on top of diced cabbage, with seam side down.
Pour cans of tomato sauce and soup over and enough water to cover.
Lay remaining 3 strips of bacon on top.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over rolls and simmer, covered, in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and simmer 30 minutes more.
Cooking time should not exceed 2 hours.
Add more water if needed.

title: phil's baco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

Place drinking glass in center of serving platter. Dip round tablespoonful of mixture to form ring around glass without touching outer edge of glass. Smooth with spatula. Remove glass. Garnish with chopped parsley or pimento.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a small casserole dish.
Cook ground beef and onion in skillet.
Spread in dish.
Top with salsa.
In a bowl, beat milk, eggs and baking mix.
Pour salsa. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions, adding 1 tablespoon coconut flavoring and 1/4 of the package of coconut.

While cake is baking, mix together evaporated milk, 4 ounces water, 1 tablespoon coconut flavoring and 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar. While cake is still hot, punch holes with fork all over cake and pour liquid mixture over cake.
After cake has completely cooled, top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep refrigerated!

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Cut marshmallows in half.
Mix pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Mix in sour cream.
When minced, fold in oranges.
Chill and serve.

title: georgia peanut cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat until fluffy. Stir in baking soda and salt.
Blend in flour and mix until a stiff dough forms.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork crosswise to flatten.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff(thrifty version)
directions: Trim fat from beef. Slice beef lengthwise into thirds. Moisten slices on each side and sprinkle with meat tenderizer, following label directions. With fork, pierce meat at 1-inch intervals to ensure tenderizer's penetration. Then cut each slice, across the grain, into 1/2-inch wide strips. Slowly heat large heavy skillet and melt 1 tablespoon butter. Add just enough beef to cover bottom of skillet.

title: banana coconut bread
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add bananas, coconut, nuts and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mix.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Turn out on plate and cover with glaze.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato sauce and water to hamburger.
(You can rinse the cans with this water.)
Stir in onion soup mix.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken in oven
directions: Bake chicken (season to taste) in covered dish until tender. Take off cover and pour out excess grease.
Spread barbecue sauce on chicken.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn chicken over and put barbecue sauce on other side.
Bake until barbecue is browned or thickened in 350° oven.

title: banana fritters
directions: Crush bananas.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk and lemon juice to crushed bananas.
Lastly add beaten egg.
Drop by tablespoon into deep fat.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans;
cover with
2 quarts water and soak overnight. Cook slowly until tender.
Drain.
Place half the beans in an earthenware pot or casserole.
Add half of the combined remaining ingredients, adding 1 cup ham broth or chunks of ham.
