Add remaining beans and seasonings.
Cover with bean broth or boiling water.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 225° to 300° at least 2 hours.
When necessary, add water.
One half can or one cup diced tomatoes may be used instead of catsup.

title: cheese bread spread
directions: Melt together cheese and butter.
Add milk and mix well.
Use as cheese spread.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Combine brown sugar dissolved in water, pineapple juice and cranberry juice in percolator.
Place cloves, cinnamon and salt in percolator basket.
Perk and serve.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil slowly for 5 minutes the first four ingredients.
Add Soda and stir in well.
Pour over Popcorn.
Put on a cookie sheet or large pan for 1 hour at 200 degrees.
Stir every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Grease tube pan. Set aside.
Melt margarine and marshmallows in a large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Press into prepared tube pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender (except pie filling) .
Mix 5 minutes, 2 minutes on puree.
Butter glass dish; put fruit on bottom.
Pour in mixture.
Top with a little cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and meat in butter or margarine.
Add salt, pepper, bouillon and water.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender.
Add additional water as needed.
Mix flour with cold water.
Stir into gravy to thicken.
Bring to simmer.
Add sour cream and simmer. Serve on buttered noodles.

title: broccoli and spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 6 ingredients together, put in large casserole and top with cheese and onion rings.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish coffee bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water and let sit until bubbly. Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour and cardamon to the cooled milk to make batter.
Add yeast and beaten eggs and beat well.
Add remaining flour, enough to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in a greased bowl.
Cover and set in a warm place and let rise until doubled in size (about 2 hours).
When light, punch down and shape.
Let rise another 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until it sounds hollow when tapped with a wooden spoon).
Use 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon water to make glaze.
Spread on top of warm bread.

title: tuna-cashew casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
In a bowl, mix together tuna, soup, celery, mushrooms, onion, soy sauce and water.
Place 1/2 can of fried noodles on bottom of casserole.
Add tuna mixture.
Add remaining noodles.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well. Add flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set.
Serve with whipped cream and strawberries, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pot roast and gravy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; rub mixture on roast.
Brown roast on both sides in hot olive oil.
Add water and next 6 ingredients. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Remove roast to platter, reserve liquid.
Remove bay leaves.
Skim fat; measure liquid, return to Dutch oven.
Combine 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons water for each cup of liquid, stir well.
Stir flour mixture into liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: glazed ham(microwave)
directions: Score top of ham and place in 10x6x1 3/4 inch baking dish. Brush on mustard and brown sugar.
Pour ginger ale on top.
Cover. Microwave, fat side down on medium high for 28 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Turn over about halfway through cooking. Allow to stand 20 to 25 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate-nut log cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk, vanilla, almond extract and egg.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: grandmother's super easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches with juice in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour cake mix over peaches and pat down. Slice margarine into pats. Spread checkerboard fashion on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Make crumbs by combining flour, sugar, shortening and salt and rubbing mixture between hands. Dissolve soda in hot water and combine with molasses.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate. Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 35
to 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add all ingredients well. Chill in the refrigerator and serve.

title: aunt gerry's spaghetti sauce
directions: Start
4 1/2 to 5 hours prior.	Saute burger and onion; drain. Put
in a large pot and add all the other ingredients. Cook
on medium heat until boiling;	reduce heat to medium low and
simmer until
meal
time,	stirring occasionally, taking care
not
to let it stick or scorch.
Serve over cooked spaghetti
noodles
and have grated American cheese and Parmesan cheese to use as toppings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in 16 ounce bag semi-sweet chocolate chips until melted.
Spread over coconut mixture on cake.
Delicious.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make to your own consistency. Refrigerate.
Will last or keep for 3 weeks.
Use on barbecue sandwich or as side dish.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Boil some flour and water.
Get it out of the water and smash it with your hands and make them round.
Put chocolate chips in. Then you eat them.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Place nuts on the bottom of a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and remove from pan.
Glaze.

title: turkey cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion & pepper together. Drain & cut cabbage. Layer cabbage, then meat, then cabbage again and pour soup on top. Bake at 350 degrees until cabbage is done (about 25-35 minutes).

title: maple nut cake
directions: Mix as any cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and set aside the cocoa mix and red food coloring.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add coloring paste and eggs; beat well. Add buttermilk, plain flour, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in vinegar by spoon.
When well blended, add soda; mix well.
Bake in well-greased and floured 8-inch layer cake pans (3).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cake completely cool before icing.

title: squash sauté
directions: Melt margarine in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add pepper.
Saut 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; saut 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender but crisp (avoid overcooking).
Yields 6 servings.

title: robbie's plum good cake
directions: *May use any kind of baby food.

title: chocolate mess
directions: Combine chocolate cake mix, oil, sour cream and eggs.
Mix well. Add pudding mix and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour in crock pot and cook on low for 6 hours.
When done serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: grilled chicken with salsa
directions: Place each chicken breast half between two sheets of heavy plastic wrap and flatten with a mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle both sides of the chicken with salt and pepper and place breasts in a shallow glass baking dish.
Combine the lime juice and oil.
Pour over the chicken.
Turn breasts to coat.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Mix well. Last, add hot oil.
Mix and pour quickly into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of two 9 x 13-inch pans with crushed wafers. Slice bananas over wafers. Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch slices over bananas. Sprinkle nuts on top. Freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and butter together. Add powdered sugar and milk.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream when cool and then freeze again.
Cover with Cool Whip and freeze. Before serving, sprinkle with nuts and top with cherries.

title: chicken and mushroom
directions: Wash and season chicken.
Fry or bake until golden brown; drain.
While chicken is frying or baking, put in Dutch oven type pan the following: soups and water.
Add mushrooms, onions, garlic and heat to boiling point.
Add cooked chicken and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in small amount of oil.
Add onion and stir for 2 minutes.
Add water and tomato sauce.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes. Don't remove lid for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut up chicken, boil and remove from bones.
Saute garlic powder, chili powder, cumin and chicken in a little chicken fat. Set aside.

title: jello dessert
directions: Pour fruit in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle Jell-O over fruit. Sprinkle on sugar. Sprinkle on cake mix.
Pour on butter.
Pour on water. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: ginger pickles
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Cut into strips 2-inches long, 1/4 x 1/2-inch wide.
(They can be cut into cubes, 1/2-inch thick, 1-inch squares or 1/4-inch thick circles.)

title: pistachio pie
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan while preheating oven to 350°. Mix in crackers.
Press on bottom; bake for 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix pudding, milk and ice cream; pour over crust.
Freeze.
When frozen, top with Cool Whip and crushed candy bars.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: salsa potato salad
directions: In bowl, combine mayo, sour cream, salsa and parsley. In large bowl, combine potatoes, celery and onion. Add dressing and toss
to coat. Stir in cheese. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate peanut butter pieces
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
In a double boiler, melt the chocolate over hot, not simmering, water.
Stir until smooth. Place the peanut butter in a small bowl; gradually beat in the sugar.
Add the peanut butter mixture to the chocolate; stir until blended.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the peanuts; spread the mixture in the foil lined pan.
Smooth the top, then sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup peanuts over the top, pressing lightly into the candy.
Chill until firm, then cut into pieces.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: pistachio pineapple delight
directions: Mix together dry pudding mix and pineapple; fold in Cool Whip. Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken elegance
directions: Spread mayonnaise on chicken.
Sprinkle the chicken with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: acapulco pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts and melted oleo and press in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Add milk according to pudding package directions.
Spread vanilla mixture over cream cheese mixture.
Spread chocolate mixture over vanilla mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat eggs and buttermilk together and set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onions.
Blend in buttermilk.
Heat fat to 375°.
Drop hush puppies a few tablespoons at a time into the fat.
Fry about 2 to 3 minutes or until evenly browned.
They will float to the surface when cooked.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve at once.

title: chicken - rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in large casserole dish over rice.
Combine soups and water; add margarine and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°; stir after 30 minutes.
Cook, uncovered.

title: egg in toast
directions: Butter one side of the bread.
Make a hole in bread.
Place in pan.
Crack egg inside of hole.
Fry till egg is cooked.
Salt and pepper to taste

title: cheese and bean dunk
directions: Cut cheese roll into chunks and place in saucepan with soup. Heat slowly, stirring constantly until blended.
Stir in sour cream with onion.
Heat.
Transfer to fondue pot.
Garnish with sliced green onions.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: butter crisp cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Melt butter in a large heavy skillet.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook, stirring until tender.
Add lemon juice, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: thai shrimp and sesame noodles
directions: Start 1 hour and 20 minutes before serving.

title: french "blender" dressing
directions: Put everything in blender.
Blend well.
Put in covered container and refrigerate.
Will keep for one month.
Makes little over 1 quart.
Great with turkey, ham, all cold cuts and burgers.

title: chinese stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions (both kinds), bamboo shoots, water chestnuts, mushrooms, broth and sugar.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1 tablespoon water and the soy sauce.
Add to mixture and simmer, stirring occasionally so it doesn't stick, until juice thickens.

title: toll house cupcakes
directions: Combine butter, 6 tablespoons brown sugar and the vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in 1 egg.
Sift flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt together; stir into creamed mixture.
Mix well. Spoon batter into 16 paper cup liners in muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat remaining egg lightly.
Add dash of salt and 1/2 cup packed brown sugar.
Beat until thick.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate bits and nuts.
Spoon mixture over cupcakes; bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Prepare brownie mix for cake-like brownies.
Grease 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Line with waxed paper, extending up sides of pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tops spring back. Cool.
In large bowl, mix milk and water; beat in pudding mix. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place 1 brownie layer on serving plate.
Top with 1/2 each of the pudding mixture and strawberries.
Repeat.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and shortening. Beat with egg beater until smooth, about 1 minute.
Don't overbeat.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan or greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: clam casserole
directions: I also add a few dried onion flakes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken and celery in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour broth and soup over this. Add salt and pepper.
Mix softened margarine, flour and milk together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is brown. Serves 6.
(Copied.)

title: swedish ham balls
directions: Combine brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Combine meats, crumbs, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls and place in a casserole.
Pour brown sugar mixture over meat balls.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste frequently with sauce.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Cook raisins with water.
Chop apples.
Combine all ingredients.
This will make 2 pies or 1 deep dish pie.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, over medium heat, saute carrots, onion, celery, potatoes, garlic and sugar in oil for 5 minutes.
Add broth, nutmeg, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Puree in batches in blender or food processor.
Return to kettle and heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onion and Tabasco. Gradually stir in tuna.
Beat until blended.
Pack in mold and chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients in blender.
Add oil, food coloring and celery seed slowly until
it thickens.
Refrigerate up to 2 weeks.

title: blueberry angel food cake rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly-roll pans with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake following package directions.
Divide batter into lined pans.
Spread evenly.
Cut through batter with knife or spatula to remove large air bubbles. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until set.
Invert cakes at once onto towels dusted with confectioners sugar.
Remove foil carefully.
Roll up each cake with towel jelly roll fashion. Cool completely.
Unroll cakes.
Spread about 1 cup blueberry pie filling to within 1-inch of edges on each cake.
Re-roll and place seam-side down on serving plate.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Put Eagle Brand milk and water in top of double boiler; mix well.
Milk will thicken as it heats up.
Stir well as chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and vanilla, mixing well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and dry strawberries.
Slice and layer into pie shell. Boil 1 cup water, then add the jello and cornstarch.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Let the jello mixture cool slightly, then pour over the strawberries.
Place in the refrigerator; let the jello set.
Cover the pie with Cool Whip.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs and butter together and place in large cake pan.
Chill.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook broccoli, zucchini, pepper, onion and basil in margarine until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and mushrooms.

title: strawberry and jello filled angel food cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Cool completely.
Cut off top of cake, about 1 to 1 1/2-inches.
Scoop out a cavity around cake, saving the pieces.
Dissolve jello with 1 cup hot water.
Add frozen strawberries and pieces of cake.
Set in refrigerator until slightly set.
Then spoon into cake cavity. Replace top.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Sift the flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Stir in the Mazola; moisten with the water.
Turn onto a floured board.
Roll and use as desired.

title: good cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dad's famous garlic slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Great with a big fish fry.

title: tuna salad cones
directions: Cook macaroni to desired doneness; drain and rinse in cool water.
Combine all ingredients except cones in a small bowl; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pick up chicken sticks
directions: Cut off tips of wings and discard.
Divide each wing in half. Melt margarine in large shallow pan.
Mix flour, seed, salt and ginger in pie pan. Roll chicken pieces, one at a time, in margarine (let excess drop off).
Roll in flour mixture to coat generally, then set aside on waxed paper until all are coated. Arrange in single layer in same pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, until richly golden bottom.
Slide pan under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes to brown.

title: lemon pudding salad
directions: Mix the box of pudding, but don't add quite as much milk, then add the remaining ingredients.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple and put in a bowl.
Mix the Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice in with the pineapple.
Mix with an electric mixer. Crush nuts and fold in.
Refrigerate.
Eat! Eat! Eat!

title: deer steak(debbie's secret)
directions: Thaw deer in vinegar mixed in bowl of water for about 4 hours; rinse well.
Cut away any white fatty film.
Sprinkle meat with tenderizer and garlic salt on each side; flour and fry.
As steak starts frying, sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon delight
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour and margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom and sides of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Cut bread in small pieces and spread over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle raisins over bread.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce or as a sandwich spread.

title: fresh coconut cake(quick)
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, poke holes all in cake with fork. While still hot, pour Eagle Brand milk over top.

title: french chocolate
directions: Combine water and chocolate squares in 1-quart measure or 1-quart glass casserole.
Cook with microwave energy, 3 to 4 minutes or until the chocolate melts.
Stir well and blend in sugar and salt.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Cool to room temperature. Fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Store in refrigerator.
To serve, place one heaping tablespoon in each cup and fill with hot milk. Stir well.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: meat balls and sauce
directions: Meat Balls:
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Brown in small amount hot fat.
Add meat balls to sauce.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joe corn bread casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion; drain.
Add chili sauce; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through.
Transfer this mixture to an 8-inch quart glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spread evenly over meat mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until corn bread top is a golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour margarine into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Now add rest of ingredients, one by one, on top of each other.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine and chopped nuts.
Then chocolate pieces over nuts and coconut over chocolate.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Allow to cool 15 minutes before cutting into finger length bars.

title: ice cream treat
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of the cookies. Drizzle syrup over.
Spread 1/2 of yogurt or ice cream.
Drizzle syrup over.
Add rest of cookies, then layer rest of yogurt or ice cream.
Drizzle syrup again, then freeze.
Spread Cool Whip just before serving.

title: diabetic rice pudding
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, combine milk, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until most of the milk is absorbed.
Stir occasionally (mixture may appear curdled.)
Stir in chopped apples.
Cool thoroughly.
Fold whipped nondairy topping into the rice mixture.
Spoon into 6 individual dessert dishes.
Chill for at least 2 to 24 hours.
If desired, sprinkle with additional ground nutmeg before serving.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion, bell pepper, pimentos and seasonings until tender. Remove chicken from broth; add spaghetti and cook until done. Drain. Add cheese; stir until melted. Debone chicken; add to spaghetti with soups and tomatoes. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hillary's cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Soften butter.
Add cocoa, then sugar; stir well.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Add vanilla, then add flour.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skillet hawaiian vegetables
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in skillet; add mushrooms and saute until golden.
Add green pepper and saute 3 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and green pepper and set aside.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet; add onions and cook until golden. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add pineapple syrup, carrots, basil, ginger, curry powder and brown sugar to onions in skillet and simmer 35 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add cooked mushrooms, green pepper, pineapple and water chestnuts and cook 5 minutes longer.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Blend together water and powdered milk.
Mix eggs, salt, vanilla and sugar together and stir into milk mixture. Add raisins and margarine.
Mix bread into liquid until lightly moistened. Bake in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat beans; brown meat.
In
a 9 x 12-inch pan, spread beans on bottom, then meat; sprinkle taco seasoning over all.
Layer onions, tomatoes, olives and sour cream.
Cover with Cheddar cheese, then Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.
Serve with taco sauce and extra sour cream, salsa and nacho chips.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until done.

title: crispy coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, 7/8 cup sugar and onion.
Heat the remaining ingredients to boiling.
Pour the hot mixture over the cabbage mixture and mix well.
Store in fruit jars in the refrigerator. The slaw gets better with age and remains crisp.
Prepare this at least one day before serving.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Remove crust from bread and grate bread into fine crumbs, using coarse side of grater.
There should be 2 cups crumbs. Spread out on flat pan to dry overnight.
Mix the crumbs with the cheese, parsley, garlic, salt, and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken into melted butter, then into the crumb mixture.
Be sure each piece is well coated.
Arrange in open, shallow roasting pan. Put remaining butter over all and bake 1 hour, until fork-tender, in 350° oven.
Do not turn, but baste frequently with pan drippings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all drained fruit and bananas.
Fold in peach pie filling and chill.

title: yogurt bundt cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing cake from pan.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soak the gelatin in the cold water. Separate the egg whites from the yolks.
Combine the beaten egg yolks with the brown sugar, spices, milk and pumpkin and cook over boiling water until custardy.
Dissolve the gelatin in the hot custard.
Cool until it begins to stiffen.

title: hot wings
directions: Separate wings and discard tips.
Lightly flour and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Heat butter, pepper sauce and garlic powder in small boiler until butter melts.
Dip cooked wings in sauce and serve warm with plenty of water.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in pan.
Chop medium onion and saute. Add 1 cup uncooked rice.
Pour in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Add beef bouillon soup and cook in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour. Do not stir.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and drizzle with margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spray 11 x 15-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour pie filling in bottom of pan and spread out over pan bottom.
Pour dry cake mix over filling evenly.
Pour melted butter over dry cake mix; then cover evenly with the pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: macadamia and coconut clusters
directions: Toast coconut on a cookie sheet in oven for about 7 minutes, stirring several times. Watch closely as it burns quickly.

title: vanilla peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between two Ritz crackers to make a sandwich cookie.
Melt vanilla milk chips according to package directions.
Once melted, remove from heat and dip peanut butter crackers into melted chips.
Lay on wax paper until hardened. Yield:
approximately 1 dozen.

title: ethel's chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Set aside.
Boil the oil, water and cocoa together and pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into cake pans and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, pour frosting over top.

title: grandma's lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water. Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boil 1 minute. Slowly stir half of hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks. Beat into remaining hot mixture.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until smooth. Blend in butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour hot filling into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Rub cottage cheese with the sugar into a paste.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Mix flour and salt.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake slowly at 250° to 300° in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, Crisco oil, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. Add flour, walnuts and apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place marshmallows on top.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion and saute until tender.
Add sliced squash, mix well, and spoon into a 1-quart casserole.
Add hard-cooked eggs and cheese; sprinkle with corn chips.
Place in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or just until cheese is melted. Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Add rest of ingredients. Heat to dissolve sugar and salt.
You may also add liquid smoke and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and a few dried onions, if desired.

title: raisin penuche icing
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and cream.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in powdered sugar until mixture is of a velvety spreading consistency.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.

title: mama's tomato preserves
directions: Skin and chop tomatoes.
Cook about 1 hour over medium heat. Add sliced lemons and sugar. Cook until thick in consistency. Skim occasionally. Delicious on toast or biscuits!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook together until sugar and margarine melt.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add meal gradually, stirring constantly.
Add salt and margarine.
Stir until creamy.
Cut off heat and add eggs.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: marinade for chicken wings or spareribs
directions: Place wings in glass baking dish.
Combine ingredients and marinate at least 4 hours, turning wings at least once or twice. Remove wings from sauce.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick mixed fruit
directions: Stir and put in your prettiest glass bowl!

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine; add oil, marshmallows and melt over low heat. Mix with M & M's, nuts and popcorn.
Put into greased tube pan and allow to set overnight.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet and cook the onion until just transparent.
Add the crumbs and blend well.
Mix with the crab meat, beaten eggs and seasonings.
Add just enough cream to hold the mixture together.
Shape into large flat cakes.
Roll each cake in flour and fry in butter or oil until nicely brown and cooked through.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix together jello in boiling water.
Add hot water and sugar to jello mixture.
Add 7 cups cold water, pineapple juice and frozen orange juice.
Mix all items together and put into ziploc freezer bags - put the empty ziploc bag into a large juice container to fill it.
Let freeze overnight, or at least for 4-5 hours.
Approximately 1 hour before serving, take out and start thawing.
Put the mixture into a punch bowl and add 2 liters of Sprite per Ziploc bag.

title: leek soup(for two)
directions: Cut leek into 1-inch sections lengthwise to make it easy to clean.
Put all ingredients into slow cooker.
Set on low, cover and let it do its work.
In microwave, put in 8-cup glass measure, cover tightly with plastic wrap and cook at 100°
for 12 minutes.

title: freeze ahead pizza crusts
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add sugar, salt and oil.
Stir in flour.
Knead for a few minutes until dough is no longer sticky. Cover and let rise.
Split dough into two pieces.
Spread dough on two well-greased pizza pans.
(Greasing your hands well makes the dough easier to work with.)
Let rise for a few minutes.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Carefully slide the partially baked dough off the pan and onto the oven rack and bake 2 to 3 more minutes until lightly browned.
The dough is now ready to put sauce, cheese, etc. on.
You may freeze it with or without the toppings.
When ready to use, preheat oven to 425° and bake about 10 minutes longer.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: In frypan, heat Crisco.
Coat chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper; fry over medium heat for 20 minutes (10 minutes each side).
Drain chicken.

title: melt in the mouth blueberry cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg whites stiff and set aside.

title: cookies made from cake mix
directions: Cream all ingredients except cake mix.
Add vanilla and cake mix.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and bake for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: egg and sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer croutons, sausage and cheese evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper in mixer bowl.
Pour over layers.
Chill, covered, overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage; drain fat.
Layer the bread, sausage and cheese in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, milk and mustard; pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Blend and melt margarine and marshmallows on stove or microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until marshmallows are puffed.
Add gelatin.
Pour mixture over popcorn and form into balls.

title: crawfish, crabmeat or shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and green onion in butter.
Add tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
Add your meat; simmer for another 20 minutes.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Mix sugar, sour cream and eggs in large mixing bowl on low (scraping bowl occasionally) for 1 minute.
Beat in bananas and vanilla on low for 30 seconds.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda on medium for 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture into pan.
Bake until light brown 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Butter Frosting.

title: turkey and noodle casserole
directions: Mix turkey and noodles.
Add pepper, cheese and eggs.
Add white sauce.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover; bake 30 minutes more.

title: five-layer dinner
directions: Butte a deep baking dish, then put the ingredients into it in the following order:
potatoes, ground beef, sliced onions, uncooked rice and tomatoes.
Season each layer.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then make meatballs about the size of walnuts.
Cook until done in skillet or in oven.
Place meatballs, green pepper and pineapple chunks in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix cornstarch, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and syrup from pineapple.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour this mixture into pan with meatballs and bake until heated through.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash or cut artichoke hearts well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with Wheat Thins or Triscuits.

title: tomato soup hot dish
directions: Cut up the peeled potatoes and carrots.
Cook until soft. Drain water.
Cut onion in rings.
Separate and add to cooked carrots and potatoes.
(May put in crock-pot.)
Take the tomato soup and pour over other ingredients.
Put in at least one can of water.
Add more, if you like it thinner.
Brown the hamburger and add to crock-pot.
Let cook in crock-pot for 1 to 2 hours.
Add desired seasonings.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Divide liquid in the pie shells.
Then divide the crumbs on top (do not stir).
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Pour into a bread pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix bars with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Next day, add apples. Chill 1 hour.
Can add mandarin oranges.
Very good and easy.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Blend well with a mixer until smooth. Serve with apple slices or strawberries.

title: cream cheese vegetable dip
directions: Cook egg, sugar and vinegar until it thickens.
When cool, add to cream cheese and pepper, onion and carrots.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except carrots.
Chop carrots and blend in blender with water.
After completely blended, remove water and fold carrots in mixture for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Put batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add water, spaghetti sauce and salt.
Bring to a boil.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer uncooked lasagna, hot sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers; end with sauce.
Garnish with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: dilled cucumber salad
directions: In bowl, whisk together vinegar, sugar and salt until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumber and toss until thoroughly coated.
Season with pepper and garnish with dill.
Cover salad with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Break half the cake into bite-size pieces; place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half the pudding over the cake, then spread 1 can crushed pineapple over the pudding.
Layer the other half of the cake pieces over that.
Next, layer remaining pudding and the other can of pineapple.
Spread the Cool Whip over the top.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into an ungreased shallow baking dish.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with oleo.
Cook pasta and broccoli according to package instructions.
Put into casserole dish and mix thoroughly with the mushroom soup.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°. (I use slotted spoon to scoop out the broccoli.)

title: hot honey
directions: Empty Mead wine into coffee pot and add spice packet.
Serve in Bola wine glass.
Add cinnamon stick for garnish.
Serve hot.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into two greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: simple and fun fruit punch
directions: Mix all liquids together and top with choice of fruit.

title: cranberry glazed pork roast
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
meat in shallow baking dish; season with salt and pepper.
Roast 20 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°; continue roasting.
In small saucepan, combine
remaining
ingredients.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until
slightly thick.
Cook meat 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Spoon half of sauce over meat.
Continue roasting until thermometer reaches 160°, basting occasionally.
Add remaining sauce, cook
10 to
minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and salt.
Blend in buttermilk.
Pour batter into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: In a bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; set aside.
In separate bowl, cut broccoli and cauliflower into small bite size florets.
Mix in cheese, onion and bacon.
Pour dressing over mixture and blend well.
Chill.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Arrange cooked and drained broccoli in 3-quart casserole. Combine cream cheese, milk and garlic salt in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Pour about half the sauce over the broccoli. Top with 1 pound sliced, cooked chicken or turkey and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Then boil until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine ingredients (use no grease).
Press thin in pan.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes, or until brown.
Set out to cool.

title: mornay sauce(turns any vegetable into a gourmet delight.)
directions: To make a roux, melt butter and stir in flour.
Add half and half and stir until thickened.
Add cheese, seasonings and wine. Stir until thick.
Pour over any combination of vegetables.

title: cousin ruby's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, milk and egg yolks.
Cook on slow heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter. Pour in baked 9-inch pie crust.

title: chili cheese puffs(makes 5 dozen appetizers)
directions: Roll both sheets of puff pastry into two 12 x 16-inch rectangles.

title: salmon pat
directions: Drain salmon well (keep bones in, excellent source of calcium).
Mash salmon and stir with a fork.
Add softened cream cheese and mix well with a fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Spray a flat bowl with cooking oil.
Pour contents into bowl and smooth out any lumps.
Refrigerate overnight.
Invert bowl over serving tray to empty contents.
Smooth out any lumps.
Serve with melba toast rounds or crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat this flour mixture with egg mixture; stir in grated zucchini.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together 2 cups sugar, 3/4 cup flour, 1/2 cup cocoa, Milnot and water.
Stir over low heat until gravy.
Separate 4 eggs and set aside whites.
Add a small amount of gravy mix to yolks, then add yolks to gravy.
Add oleo and 2 teaspoons vanilla to gravy. Cook for a few minutes stirring continuously.
Pour into cooked pie crust.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine frozen corn, potato, onion, water, bouillon granules and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until corn and potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of milk and margarine.
Combine the remaining milk and flour. Stir milk-flour mixture into corn mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
If desired, garnish with snipped chives or parsley and crisp-cooked, crumbled bacon.
Serves 4 to 6 side-dishes.

title: quiche
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Put in greased pie pan and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and softened margarine.
Add beaten eggs, then add buttermilk, vanilla, flour and meal.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Begin baking at 400°, then turn to 325° after about 10 or 15 minutes, when pie begins to brown.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until pie no longer "jiggles."

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients the night before.
Squeeze lemons to make 1 cup of juice.
Cut up lemon rinds and add to sauce or grind them and add.
Bring to boiling point.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Bring to boiling just before using.
Brush on chicken and grill.

title: grape muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, brown sugar and nutmeg in a mixing bowl. Mix well.
Beat egg until frothy; mix in milk and butter.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in grapes. Turn batter into 12 well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange layers in order given.
Do not mix.
Cover with mayonnaise completely and sprinkle with sugar.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add oil, water and strawberries.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Divide batter into two 8 or 9-inch pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: instant tea
directions: Mix water and proper amount of instant tea mix.
Add pineapple juice and almond flavoring.
Mix and serve cold.
Great for parties or brunch.

title: cake bars
directions: Cut into cake mix 1/2 cup soft butter; press into bottom of cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until browned.
Spread crushed fruit on top and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1/2 hour.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate awhile.

title: pat's fruit dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until smooth.
Use as a dip for sliced apples, strawberries and other fruits.

title: webb's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add the other ingredients and mix.
Put in a gallon plastic bag (mash down 3 times).
Put in refrigerator; will keep for 4 or 5 days.
Form into rolls about 1 to 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 350°.

title: kicked up burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into hamburger patties and cook on grill.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ground beef and tomato paste. Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour.
Brown ground beef; drain and add to soup with tomato paste and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: ultimate brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; add sugar, flour, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon tater bites
directions: According to the number of snacks you need, cook half strips of bacon until lightly browned but still limp.
Meanwhile prepare frozen Ore-Ida Tater Tots according to package directions.
Cut slices of American cheese into thirds and wrap a strip of cheese around each hot Tater Tot.
Wrap limp bacon around the cheese and secure with a toothpick.
Broil, turning once, until bacon is crisp. Serve hot with mustard sauce.
Mix mustard, brown sugar and ginger together to make mustard sauce.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Prepare a chocolate cake mix and bake in greased 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Cool.
Break up cake in a large bowl.
Pour 2/3 cup of Kahlua over cake mixture and let soak all day.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine bread crumbs and water.
Let soak for 5 minutes.
Peel onion.
Grate finely.
In another bowl, combine meat, grated onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Add crumb mixture. Combine until well blended.
Roll meat mixture into even meatballs with hands.
In a skillet, heat butter until melted and lightly browned.
Add meatballs, a few at a time.
Shake pan constantly and cook meatballs until brown all around and cooked through. Remove.

title: fish whirls
directions: Make fillets into rolls; season and add a squeeze of lemon juice.
Put onto deep pan with 1 ounce butter and little milk. Bake about 20 minutes, until just tender.
Fill rolls with shrimp half-way through the cooking.
Remove fish to hot serving dish. Keep hot.
Heat rest of butter.
Stir in flour and cook a few minutes.
Strain liquid from cooking fish.
Add to the "roux" with remaining milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until thickened; season well and stir in cream.
Pour around fish.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: hearty burgundy meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Shape mixture into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Over medium heat, heat oil; add meatballs.
Cook about 12 minutes, turning frequently, until well browned on all sides.
Remove meatballs to plate.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: zucchini soup
directions: If zucchini skin seems tough, peel them.
If zucchini seeds are large, scoop them out.

title: world's best almond cheesecake
directions: Spray with Pam.
Mix all ingredients until very fluffy.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add to cooled cake and bake another 10 to 12 minutes.
Refrigerate (sprinkle slivered almonds on top) several hours before serving.

title: jean's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Dice other vegetables.
Saute in a very large frypan or wok in 1/2 stick margarine and 2 tablespoons cooking oil until vegetables are tender.
Butter 13 x 9-inch pan. Put 1/2 vegetables in pan and 1 cup grated cheese.
Repeat remaining vegetables.
Add 1 cup cheese; sprinkle top with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown and cheese melts.

title: shenandoah apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and fill 9-inch pie plate pastry shell.
Cover with top crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in greased tube pan 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mandarin jello salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water; put ice cubes in and stir until jello begins to jell.
Take ice out.
Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: party sausages
directions: You will need a crock-pot or large pot.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks, flavoring and sugar; mix well.
Add canned milk.
Stir.
Pour in shell.
Bake 30 minutes or until solid at 350°.

title: water chestnut salad
directions: Mix the lettuce, celery, onion and water chestnuts with thawed English peas.
Combine mayonnaise and powdered sugar.
Mix with salad.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.

title: frozen yogurt pops
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor and mix until berries are cut into large chunks.
Pour into ice cube trays.
Cover tray with waxed paper and insert toothpicks into center of each cube as holders.
(You can use home ice-pop molds.) Yield varies depending on mold used.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the soups and milk together, seasoning with garlic, pepper and salt to taste.
Place chicken in casserole and pour mixture over it.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing, rolled out fine.
Dot with very small pats of butter.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add butter and season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken empadon
directions: Mix 4 cups flour and mayonnaise and pat into a pre-buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, patting on the bottom and up the sides.
Add the chicken and vegetable mixture.* Top with remaining pastry mixture.
Brush gently with beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cracker jack popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in large
pan (dishpan).
Mix sugar, margarine and syrup in saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix until well coated.
Put into large roaster pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Pour on waxed paper to cool. Break apart and store in airtight container.
Yield:
8 to 9 quarts.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to bowl; cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard and salt to chilled rice; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir in the remaining ingredients before serving.
Serves 6.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt fat; add onion and rice.
Saute until golden.
Add bouillon.
Cook until rice is done.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce. In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of buttered tortillas, meat sauce, olives and cheese.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
In saucepan, bring milk and butter to boil.
Mix all the ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour milk and butter ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Batter will be very runny.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: In 3-quart pan over high heat and in 1-inch of boiling water, cook carrots for 1 minute (or longer).
Add broccoli, cauliflower and celery.
Cook 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Drain immediately and cool vegetables under cold running water; drain.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed; let it cool.
Crumble half of the cake in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 can pineapple, strawberries, 1/2 package of strawberry glaze and 1 tub Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Do not mix. Leave in layers and serve as is.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Toss gently while warm.
May add seasoned salt to taste.

title: pickled sweet peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut them in half.
Remove core and seeds. Slice peppers in 1/4-inch strips.
In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water and pickling salt.
Bring to a boil. Add sliced peppers and return to a boil.
Remove from heat. Place a clove of garlic in each hot, sterilized pint jar.
Use tongs to immediately fill jars with hot peppers.
Fill jars with brine, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Carefully run a nonmetallic utensil down inside of jars to remove trapped air bubbles.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 5 minutes. Yield: 6 pints.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, pour cold milk, water and raw rice. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Lower heat and simmer, stirring often (stir in the thin crust that forms on top of mixture).
Cook for about 45 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Remove from heat and let stand while you mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir eggs slowly into the cooked rice, using a wooden spoon.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 35 minutes

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter; add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to previous mixture and mix well.
Roll in long logs.
Wrap in foil and place in refrigerator or freezer.
Make up more than 1 batch and put in freezer until ready to bake.
Then take out, slice and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal snap cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients then drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Simply mix together.
If too thick, it can be thinned with skim milk.
This can also be used for potato chips or corn chips.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Combine cereal and milk; let stand about 3 minutes or until cereal softens.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Pour batter into 12 lightly-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a large sauce pan.
Remove from heat, add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with a spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 24 brownies.

title: bizcochitos
directions: Beat lard and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Mix in rum, salt, baking soda, baking powder, and anise flavoring. Add flour, a little at a time, and mix until well blended.
Using a melon ball scoop, place spoonfuls of dough on an ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo. Add all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: heart-shaped pan cookie
directions: Beat butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes; cool.
Melt remaining chocolate chips and spread over cookie.
Chill for 30 minutes or until chocolate is set.
Use heart-shaped pan or regular cake pan.

title: cheesy zucchini fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a large mixing bowl. Stir in zucchini, cheese, and onion; set mixture aside. Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened. Carefully drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls into 1 inch hot oil (375°).
Cook only a few at a time, turning once. Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until fritters are golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yield:
about 2 dozen.

title: pasta in a pot(very good and easy)
directions: Cook beef; add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Next, alternate layers in order:
1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 of sour cream and 1/2 of the 2 cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Then uncover and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted through.
Serves 15.

title: alice's lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cold water and rest of ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: indian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in water.
Add egg, oleo and sugar to yeast mix. Add flour to mix.
Store in refrigerator in airtight bowl.
Bake in muffin tins.
Grease pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick with mixer.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix by hand until well blended.

title: parmesan chicken #1
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Then dip in mixture of sour cream and the beaten egg.
Then dip in mixture of Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs (add salt and pepper, if desired).
Place in buttered oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and tender.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour in casserole dish. Spoon topping over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: milk caramels
directions: Heat sugar and syrup in 1 cup milk, stirring until dissolved. Cook, stirring frequently, to 246° to 248°, or until firm ball stage.
Slowly add second cup of milk and repeat the cooking process.
Add the final cup of milk, the butter and salt.
Cook to 246° to 248°, or until a firm ball stage in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour at once into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour croutons on bottom of dish, spreading evenly. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
In skillet, brown sausage until crumbly; drain.
Spoon sausage over cheese. Sprinkle mushrooms over sausage.
Combine eggs, dry mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Beat well.
Pour over sausage. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Combine the mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: whacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cocoa.
Add to dry ingredients the vegetable oil, vinegar, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chocolate coconut slices
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift together the flour and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well. Stir walnuts into batter.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Combine milk and coconut; spread over hot cake and return to oven.
Continue baking until coconut is lightly browned, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spray 8 inch square pan. Peel and cut up apples. Wrap 1 quarter apple in roll. Put in pan. Melt margarine, add cinnamon and sugar. pour over rolls. Pour drink over rolls. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese up in small pieces or use singles.
Brown beef; drain off fat.
Put beef and rest of ingredients in crock-pot and stir.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, stirring often until cheese is completely melted.
Serve immediately or turn on low for up to 6 hours.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: banana frozen salad
directions: Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and freeze.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan, or use paper baking cups.
Combine ingredients.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: granny cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix in baking powder, flour and vanilla.
Melt margarine in milk and add to mix slowly.
Pour in greased, floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken taco pie
directions: Boil chicken until meat comes away from the bone easily.
Save 1 cup of the broth. Combine broken chicken pieces, soups, sauce and onion.
Heat until hot.
While heating, put a layer of tortilla chips in baking dish.
Pour taco stuff over chips.
Add another layer of chips.
Cover with shredded cheese of choice. Pour chicken broth over this.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter mixing with all ingredients.
Heat in oven for 1 hour.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Layer as listed.
Season each layer. Cover and bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Season chicken as desired.
Mix Butter Buds per directions. Dip chicken in Butter Bud mixture.
Roll in Rice Krispies.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 4 pieces.
Combine flour and salt, sprinkle into meat (use remaining flour for sauce).
Brown meat in hot Crisco. Transfer meat into shallow baking dish.
Blend reserved flour mixture in pan drippings in skillet.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots, onions and Worcestershire sauce into drippings and cook. Stir constantly until it boils.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and margarine; add eggs and mix well. Spread out into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan, batter will be stiff.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together. Pour over first layer (will have to spread out over the first layer).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cake will be soft in the middle when hot.

title: asparagus side dish
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and saute onion and asparagus for 3 minutes on high.
Add water or butter if needed.
Add mushrooms and light cream and cook for 1 minute.

title: sausage balls
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: creamy chicken and gravy
directions: Brown chicken breasts in skillet. Add cream of chicken soup and water (just enough water to make gravy). Add lemon pepper and salt to taste. Cook rice or noodles; drain and rinse. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: strawberry rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir baking powder and salt into flour.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour mixture to batter in thirds, alternating with milk.

title: chess pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs.
Melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.

title: diced beets *
directions: Dice beets in small bowl and set aside.
In small saucepan, add sugar, flour, a little beet water and vinegar, one at a time until all is in.
Add salt.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Pour over beets and mix.

title: red cinnamon pickles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to a boil (dissolve sugar) and pour over red cucumbers.
Let stand until next day in the solution (18 to 24 hours).
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in hot, sterilized jars.
Place in water bath of boiling water for 5 minutes.
Place in cool, dark place.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Drain beans and divide into 4 servings.
Wrap each with a strip of bacon and secure
with
a
toothpick.
Place
in
a baking
dish
and sprinkle
with
lemon
juice.
Mix
dressing according to directions and pour over beans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, then at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and sugar in bowl and blend well. Press crumbs into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: light cream whip
directions: In small deep bowl, dissolve gelatin and cold water over hot water, then add 1 cup light cream and dash of salt.
Place in a larger bowl of ice and water and whip or beat for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: larapin cake
directions: Cream butter.
Melt chocolate.
Add salt and sugar to butter; mix well.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Add egg yolks and chocolate to butter.
Add coffee; mix well.
Beat egg whites until firm and fold into chocolate mixture.
Cut cake into 5 horizontal layers.
Spread each layer with chocolate mixture, then entire cake.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: low-fat crunchy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Western dressing, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon chili powder and onion powder. Reserve 1/3 cup of sauce.

title: sweet sour slaw
directions: Boil Crisco, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over the cabbage mixture.
Let set until chilled.
Keeps for days in refrigerator.

title: creamy peach dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine peaches with sugar, lemon juice and salt; add this to gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Line a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Pour gelatin mixture into pan; chill overnight.
Garnish with fresh peaches.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl at medium speed until frothy.
Add sugar, beating well.
Stir in chocolate syrup, vanilla and salt. Pour into freezer can of a 1 1/2-gallon, hand-turned or electric ice cream freezer.
Add whipping cream and milk, stirring well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ice cream ripen 1 hour before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat
egg yolks; add sugar and cornstarch or flour, and mix thoroughly.
Add
milk
and
cook in a double boiler until creamy, stirring
constantly.
Remove
from
the heat and add vanilla. Place
alternate layers of wafers and sliced bananas in
baking dish.
Pour custard over bananas and wafers.
Beat egg whites until
stiff and sweeten with 4 tablespoons sugar. Spread over pudding and brown in 350° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain water from vegetables. Mix all ingredients together (except butter and cracker crumbs). Pour into dish. Mix together butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle on top of vegetable mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix the hamburger, egg, milk, chili powder, salt and rice together and form into balls, 1 1/2-inches.
Brown in a bit of oil.
Boil the remaining ingredients together and drop in the meatballs.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 24 balls.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients 2 hours before serving.
Add others just before serving.

title: death by chocolate(dietetic)
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Crumble the baked cake and place 1/3 in large bowl.
Add 1/3 previously made pudding.
Add 1/3 Cool Whip.
Continue for 2 more layers. Serve cold.

title: queen's salad
directions: Mix in order and chill overnight.

title: robbie's squash casserole
directions: Melt
oleo
and
pour
over herb dressing mix.	Combine half of	the
dressing
mix
with the rest of the ingredients. Put into 2 quart dish.
Top with the rest of the dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade corn dogs
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Heat hot dogs through and through.
Roll in flour mixture.
Dip in hot, hot oil until brown.

title: baked roast
directions: Brown roast on top of stove; save stock for gravy.
Put roast in baking pan; add 2 to 3 cups water.
Add vegetables; cover.
Let cook 4 to 5 hours.
Make gravy and add to meat and vegetables. Add more water if needed.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Blend the first four ingredients in a blender until smooth. Pour into crust and refrigerate for at least one hour.
Top with fresh or canned fruit.
Fresh strawberries are especially good.

title: french dressing
directions: Put together in pint jar and shake well.
Refrigerate.
Shake again before using.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion and green chilies.
Add dry ingredients and stir until meat is well coated.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes.

title: dietetic oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Whip nonfat dry milk with ice water until stiff peaks form (4 to 5 minutes).
Boil raisins in water for 2 minutes; drain; reserve liquid for later use.
Combine butter, Sugar Twin, egg and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add liquid from boiled raisins.
Then add dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Stir in rolled oats and raisins.
Fold in whipped nonfat dry milk.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger together and drain. Add spices and Velveeta and heat until cheese is melted. Spread on party rye bread and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add the Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients until moist.
Spread mixture in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: pig cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, oranges and juice, eggs and oil.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and frost.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Rinse in cold water. Drain well.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, zucchini, olives, onions, mushrooms, cauliflower and broccoli.
Cover and chill several hours.
At serving time, toss with tomato and 2/3 cup low or nonfat Italian or Ranch dressing.

title: round steak with green peppers
directions: Coat meat in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown meat on all sides.
Drain tomatoes, reserving both tomatoes and liquid.
Add liquid, onion, garlic and broth to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and pepper strips.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan cake bars
directions: Prepare cake
mix
as directed on package.
Pour batter into two greased
x 10 x 1-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Meanwhile,
cream
butter and sugar together. Mix in pecans.
While
cakes are still warm, spread each with pecan topping.
Place
cakes
under
broiler
until topping is bubbly. Cut each cake into bars.

title: good pie crust
directions: Pour water over lard and stir until melted; then stir in the flour and salt.
Set in refrigerator to cool, at least 1/2 hour. Makes 2 pies or 4 crusts.

title: cream chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash, covering pieces of chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pour off liquid and mix with soup.
Pour over chicken and return to oven for gravy to heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip whites with 6 tablespoons sugar.
Place in refrigerator.
Cream softened butter and add sugar gradually. Add egg yolks two at a time.
Stir in flour and cream alternately. Add flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites (this is important). Bake in greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, crackers, onions and remaining ingredients. Fry shaped patties in 1 tablespoon shortening.
After meat is done, remove from pan.

title: fat-free green beans
directions: Drain and rinse green beans.
Place beans, onion and celery seed in pan.
Cover with water and boil for 5 minutes.
Cover pan and cook on low for approximately 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: whisper dessert(a luscious concoction for guests)
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
While eating dinner, freeze (1/2 hour).
Re-blend and serve in small, fancy glasses.

title: anytime quiche
directions: Set crust aside to thaw.
In skillet, saute next 4 ingredients.
Cook until all is soft.
Add spinach souffle; cook until all is hot.
While this is cooking, heat pie crusts for 2 minutes. Mix eggs and milk in blender.
Place meat mixture in crust.
Cover with cheese evenly.
Add egg mixture.
Pat down cheese with fork.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: ruth's barbecue
directions: Put all ingredients in roasting pan.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Stir a little every hour.
When completely cooked, mash with potato masher.
Serve on buns or kaiser rolls.
(This recipe freezes well.)

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chinese new years cookies
directions: Melt chips and paraffin.
Add nuts and noodles.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls.
Can substitute potato sticks for noodles.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut fish into 2-inch squares.
In a large saucepan, bring 2 cups water to boil.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in fish, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: gorpe
directions: Mix first four ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add mixture to Cheerios and peanuts.
Bake on a buttered sheet pan or large roasting pan at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen with spatula.
Leave set for one hour to cool.
Then add one package of M & M's and break up in pieces. Store in a sealed container.

title: old fashion butter rolls
directions: Roll dough.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Roll and cut; place in deep baking pan.
Add boiling water to cover dough.
Bake until brown.

title: oyster corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Layer crackers, corn mixture, oysters, crackers, corn mixture and oysters.
Top with crackers.
In a 2-quart casserole, bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crackers are golden brown.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on salad greens, if desired.

title: lebkuchen(german recipe from grandma hartmeyer)
directions: Day before:
Combine candied fruits, cherries and raisins. Cover and let stand overnight.

title: basic cheese sauce(low-fat)
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in cornstarch and pepper; add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, then cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Add cheese, stirring to melt. Makes about 1 1/2 cups or 24 (1 tablespoon) servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a saucepan and bring slowly to the boiling point, stirring frequently.
Let the mixture cook slowly until it is golden in color and forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from the heat and add Marshmallow Whip, butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until nearly stiff and pour it into a greased pan.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix the flour, sugar and beer until well blended.
Pour into pan; bake for 30 minutes.
Remove pan from oven; pour melted butter over top. Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes or more, until brown. Serve warm.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form into 2 loaves.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken up; salt and pepper; roll in flour and fry until browned.
Drain off grease.
Combine water, hot pepper, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, margarine and mustard.
Bring barbecue sauce to a boil and pour over chicken.
Reduce heat to simmer chicken at medium heat.
Can be used for spareribs or pork chops.

title: tangy sweet macaroni salad
directions: Mix in small bowl with whisk the sugar	and
the mayonnaise. Mix well and add the vinegar.
Mix	well
with
whisk until it no longer looks curdled.
Add	scallions.
Pour
over cooked macaroni and mix well.
Refrigerate	24 hours, covered. Remove 30 minutes before serving and garnish	with eggs, green peppers and chopped pimentos.
Serve on greens.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients. Serve chilled.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain vegetables in a colander at least 2 hours.
Place in mixing bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and paprika and pour over vegetables and mix gently.
Place in glass container and chill.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain all drippings except 2 tablespoons.
Saute the onion in the reserved drippings, until tender.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the ingredients.
Begin with 1/2 of the bread, then 1/2 the sausage, 1/2 onion and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
