Beat together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard, then pour over the layers. Cover; refrigerate for at least overnight before cooking.
When ready to bake, remove baking dish from refrigerator 1 hour before baking to bring to room temperature, then bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: surprise salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and 3/4 cup fruit juice. Cut fruit into small pieces; add to jello mix.
Stir in ice cream; place in mold.
Add all ingredients.
Fruit ends on bottom with a white top.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together. Add pet milk, margarine and vanilla. Bring to a boil and cook until soft ball stage (234) degrees. Remove from heat and beat with electric mixer until creamy. Pour in buttered dish and refrigerate until it sets.

title: dough art
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape to roll shapes (such as cinnamon rolls, brush with egg white and sprinkle on cinnamon).
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Let cool in oven.
Glue on miniature magnets and use on refrigerator and for decorations.

title: salami dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese and soup.
Mix well.
Add chopped salami.
For best results, leave refrigerated overnight. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: a german meal - one pot meal
directions: In large pot, place the pigs feet (or roast) and cook until almost done, about 2 hours.
Then place potatoes (peeled and cut in half) in pot and let cook until done.
Then cut cabbage into 4 parts and place in pot with potatoes and pork and cook until done. You can serve with bread or just before you serve take everything from the pot and make dumplings in broth.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes and boil in skins.
Cool. (Okay to refigerate for cooling.) Peel and grate on medium grater.
Mix salt, pepper and onion with grated potatoes.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter; put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and pour over rice.
Arrange green pepper slices over rice.
Cover tightly with foil and put in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Saute meat; add onion, celery and garlic and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes; stir in tomato sauce.
Remove pan from oven and spoon meat mixture over rice and pepper.
Cover and bake 15 to 30 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 5 minutes, uncovered. Serves 6.

title: sparkling champagne punch
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Chill well.
To serve punch, pour the juice mixture over ice in a large punch bowl.
Gently stir in ginger ale, tonic water and champagne.
Yield:
1 1/2 gallons.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Thaw frozen shrimp.
Cut large shrimp in half.
Blend flour into fat and brown, stirring constantly.
Add water gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: bonbons temptation pie
directions: Crush cookies.
Combine with butter.
Press into buttered 8-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all except butter and crackers.
Crush crackers.
Melt butter or margarine.
Mix crushed crackers and butter together. Put on top.
At 350°, bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate truffle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375° and grease cookie sheets.
Cream the butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Add flour and salt at low speed.
Fold in chips by hand.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.

title: cream cheese pine cone
directions: Spread almonds in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Let cool.
Combine ingredients except almonds.
Cover and chill overnight.
Form into 2 pine cone shapes.
Beginning at narrow end, press almonds into mixture at a slight angle in rows, overlapping until covered.
Garnish with a sprig of pine.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and fruit cocktail in large serving bowl.
Whip cream until stiff.
Add sugar.
Fold whipped cream into fruit mixture.
Let set for a few hours.
When ready to serve, fold in bananas and sprinkle coconut on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: miracle pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and add pecans, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar. Add vanilla and eggs. Add oatmeal and nuts. Mix well. Line cookie sheet with foil. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon, 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes. Let cookies cool somewhat before removing from foil, they will be very thin and lacy.

title: creamed potatoes with eggs(a very old recipe)
directions: Cut the potatoes and eggs in thick slices. Place a layer of potatoes in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cover with a layer of eggs. Repeat and pour over white sauce. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bella asparagus
directions: Steam asparagus until tender-crisp; drain.

Make dressing with oil, vinegar, garlic powder, parsley flakes, salt and pepper. While asparagus is hot, layer half the spears in a deep dish. Sprinkle half the chopped eggs and bacon bits over asparagus and half the dressing.
Make a second layer of asparagus spears.
Top with remaining chopped eggs, bacon bits and dressing.
Serve at room temperature or chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Heat milk in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat until hot. Combine 1 1/3 cups sugar, flour and salt. Gradually add sugar mixture to milk, stirring until blended. Cook mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly, 15 minutes or until thickened. Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot milk mixture into beaten eggs; add to remaining hot milk mixture, stirring constantly. Cook 1 minute or until temperature reaches 160°; remove from heat and cool. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Whip egg yolks until pale yellow and very fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk; slowly add lime juice and rind.
Pour into graham crust pie shell.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: date bars
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together until thick; cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Spread 1/2 mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch or 7 x 11-inch greased pan, pat lightly.
Spread with cooled date mixture.
Cover with remaining dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash greens thoroughly several times.
Throw away any yellow leaves or heavy stems.
Cook meat covered with water (about 20 minutes).
Cut the greens into small pieces.
Add greens and bring to a hard boil.
Cover and lower heat and cook slowly for 2 hours or until tender.
Add peeled and diced turnips on top of greens for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Put jello in bowl and add water to dissolve.
Add strawberries. (Save a couple to decorate top.)
Stir until jello thickens separating strawberries.
Fold in cool whip.
Put a little cool whip on top with strawberries to decorate.

title: shrimp and eggplant casserole
directions: Cover eggplant with water and cook until tender but not mushy; drain and cool. Cut in two lengthwise. Scoop out inside. Place shells in baking dish. Cut up eggplant pulp. Saut in small amount of olive oil the onion, green pepper, parsley and garlic. Mix all ingredients together and fill eggplant shells. Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake, uncovered (add very small amount of water to bottom of baking dish) at 300° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Scrape carrots and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Cook in salted water until tender; cool.
Add chopped pepper and sliced onions which have been separated into rings.
Cover with sauce made of soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Drain and serve.
Will keep several days.
Use as needed.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with salt and pepper, stirring often.
Add soup mix, noodles and water.
Cover and cook 25 minutes.
Uncover and add sour cream and cream of mushroom soup; stir well.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes more.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs (slightly beaten) and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix (by hand evenly) over mixutre.
Pour melted margarine over cake evenly.
Top with chopped nuts.
Cut in squares to serve.
Best done day before serving, as it take a while to cool.
Cut when cool.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: chinese chicken with peppers and onions
directions: Cut chicken, green and red peppers and onions into 1-inch squares.
In a wok or large frying pan, heat 2 tablespoons of corn oil until begins to smoke.
Add ginger, hot peppers and chicken. Stir until chicken is cooked (5 minutes).
Remove to a serving dish.
Add 2 more tablespoons oil.
Add green peppers and onions; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Return chicken.
Add soy sauce; stir 1 minute.
Sprinkle with sesame hot oil.
Serve with rice.

title: cheese straws
directions: *Leave out of refrigerator several hours.

title: aloha chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, garlic salt, onion powder, ginger and paprika to make a baste.
Brush over chicken.
Bake 30 mins.
Turn once. (You may grill chicken if desired.)
Combine pineapple and juice with ketchup, brown sugar, and soy sauce.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Continue baking or grilling for 15 more mins.
Turn chicken; spoon on more sauce, bake 15 more min., or until done.

title: eugenia's fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and evaporated milk to a rolling boil. Boil exactly 8 minutes, stirring constantly from the beginning. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate and chocolate bits.
Add marshmallow cream and nuts.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown meat and drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper. Set this aside. Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds. Spoon meat mixture inside of peppers.
Arrange in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Just before they are done, add strips of cheese on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix coffee with 1 cup boiling water and set aside. Bring other cup of water and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly. Add coffee and vanilla; let cool. Add alcohol. Fill bottle 3/4 full, then fill with water. Shake prior to using.

title: hoedown taters
directions: Slice potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Combine potatoes, cheese, sour cream and margarine.
Mix until blended.
Stir in bacon.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fill shells.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples into a greased 8-inch pan. Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix together, in a 2-quart saucepan, sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil, then time 5 minutes exactly. Remove and quickly beat in marshmallow cream, vanilla and chocolate, then add nuts.
Pour immediately into buttered dish. Let stand for 1 1/2 hours, then slice and place on platter.
Never refrigerate!

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine all ingredients, except macaroni. Cover and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
I cooked my macaroni before, then I add it to the soup which has been brought to a boil and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Yields 5 to 8 servings. Delicious!

title: creamy mushroom steaks(microwave)
directions: Cut room temperature steak into strips across the grain.
Place in microwave dish and sprinkle with crushed beef cube.
Cover. Microwave at High for 3 minutes, turning beef after 2 minutes.

title: flounder au gratin
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan on low heat.
Add onions and celery.
Saute until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Stir well. Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Lower heat and cook until cheese melts. Set aside.
Drain fillets and arrange in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until fish flakes easily.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Serve.
Yield: 4 servings of 164 calories each.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Peel stems and slice thin.
Mix broccoli, onion, bacon and cheese.
To make dressing, mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Toss salad with dressing.

title: michael's favorite potato soup
directions: Melt butter over low heat and add flour gradually.
Stir until no longer lumpy.
Add liquids, gradually stirring.
Stir until no lumps are left.
Add next 3 ingredients and season to taste.
Stir until comes to a boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and let simmer until potatoes are done.
Makes 12 servings.
Contains 190 calories, 2 grams fat.

title: crumble for the top of fish fillets
directions: Combine with the butter all of the ingredients.
Broil fish covered with butter; turn and spread with mixture.
Broil 2 or 3 minutes or until brown.
Garnish with lemon and parsley.

title: sesame sticks
directions: Trim off bread crusts; cut in 5 strips and place on cookie sheet, not touching.
Bake at 200° for 30 minutes.
Remove and brush with melted butter on all 4 sides.
Roll in cheese, then in seed.
Place on cookie sheet not touching.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Chop and slice fruit. Pour sherry over and let sit, covered, for 24 hours, overnight anyway.
Stir occasionally.

title: rosy glow punch
directions: Place water in a large saucepan.
Add sugar and heat until dissolved.
Add juices and cinnamon sticks.
Simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Serve warm with orange slices and cinnamon sticks in each cup.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Add beans with juice, tomatoes with juice and Polish sausage in chunks. Add bell peppers and onion all together in a pot. Bring to a boil. Add cornstarch and water to thicken. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook rice as instructed. Serve over rice.

title: alligator tail with lemon butter sauce
directions: Thinly slice the meat and remove all fat.
Broil for 10 to 15 minutes, about 6-inches from the heating element.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Heat syrup (do not boil). Pour over bacon drippings (*or oleo). Add baking soda, salt, ginger and flour. Roll, cut and cook at 325°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade
and
Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix well.	Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill until firm.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients. Turn dough onto lightly floured board. Shape dough into ball with lightly floured hands, pressing to make dough compact. Cut dough in half. Shape each half into roll 2-inches in diameter and about 8-inches long by gently rolling dough back and forth on floured board. Roll dough onto plastic wrap; wrap and twist ends tightly. Dough can be refrigerated up to 1 month or frozen up to 3 months.

title: creamy chocolate pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in milk and egg yolk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook one additional minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Beat all together until blended.
Place cup cake liners in pan, then put one vanilla wafer in liner.
Put cheese filling in (2 tablespoons).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool put one teaspoon filling (cherry pie filling, blueberry pie filling or crushed pineapple) on top.
Makes 12 large or 24 mini cup cakes.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and salt until hard ball is made in cold water.
Pour hot mixture over marshmallow cream and blend, then add vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Spoon out on foil or wax paper.

title: rice krispies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in medium saucepan until melted. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Spread in pan, then cut.

title: pot au feu
directions: Take a good size beef bone with plenty of meat on it.
Extract the marrow bone, crack it, and place all in large pot, covering with cold water; cover tightly.
Allow to simmer slowly all day long.
The next day, before heating, remove the cake of grease from the top.
Add a large onion, previously stuck full of whole cloves and roasted in the oven until a rich brown color.
Add any other vegetables you wish.
Rice or vermicelli may be added.
Just before serving, put a little brown sugar and stir through it. This gives a peculiar and rich color to the soup.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes to an hour.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Take chicken out after boiling.
Put spaghetti into that water and boil until done.

title: diabetic chocolate mounds
directions: Melt chocolate in heavy pan over low heat, add raisins and rice cereal. Stir to coat. Drop onto cookie sheet covered with waxed paper. Chill. Once chilled, keep at room temperature.

title: danish coffee cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add salad oil.
Mix well, then remove 3/4 cup of the mixture for the topping.
To 3/4 cup of flour mixture, add nuts and cinnamon.
Mix, then set aside.
To remaining flour mixture, add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in kettle 3 minutes or until soft.
Stir in flour, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring 2 minutes.
Stir in broth, carrots and potatoes.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until almost boiling.
Do not boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add pepper and salt, if you wish.
Garnish with extra cheese.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak
beans
overnight.
Then cook beans until done.
In frypan
add
pepper,
onion,
garlic
and
sausage;
cook until tender.
Add
to red beans and let cook on low heat about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook rice as stated on box.
Drain rice and rinse. Pour beans over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hearty potato soup(my favorite soup)
directions: In large pan, cook potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in water until tender.
Do not drain off water.
Put in enough water to cover everything.

title: instant party potatoes
directions: In saucepan, bring water, margarine and salt to a boil.
Add milk, cream cheese, sour cream, garlic powder and onion; stir in instant potatoes.
Spoon into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel green off rind, also all pink on thick rind.
Place in gallon jar.
Pour vinegar over to cover rind.
Cover jar with cloth and let set 6 weeks.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg in the milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Let mixture set for 10 to 15 minutes. Drop one tablespoon at a time in hot oil (350°).
Fry until golden.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Mix together bouillon, 1 qt. water and vegetables and cook. Add soup and 1/2 can of water. Cook till boiling. Take soup from heat and stir in 1 lb. velveeta cheese until melted.

title: apple roll
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, shortening, salt and milk to biscuit consistency.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread with finely chopped apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up as jelly roll. Cut into one-inch sections and place in pan lined with 1 cup sugar and 1/3 cup butter, melted.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Then add remaining ingredients and pour into greased and floured (2) loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients except sugar. Combine corn oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Gradually add dry ingredients. Mix well. Add carrots. Pour into three 8-inch greased pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple soda
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender. Blend until smooth. Stir in club soda. Serve immediately. Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: lynette's hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop both kinds of artichoke hearts and put in greased casserole dish.
Layer chiles on top.
Spread mayonnaise on chiles.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with king size chips.
A great side dish when grilling burgers!

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, mustard, vinegar and celery seed in blender.
Slowly add salad oil while blending.
Add poppy seed and food coloring.
Keeps well in a refrigerator.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil for 10 minutes. Drop peaches in syrup and cook until tender. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: perch dinner
directions: Drain olives, reserving juice.
Add enough milk to reserved liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Saute onion in melted butter in skillet.
Blend in next 4 dry ingredients.
Heat until mixture bubbles; remove from heat.
Add liquid gradually, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Alternate layers of half the fillets, cheese and almonds in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour 2/3 of the sauce over top.
Cover with overlapping layers of potatoes and remaining sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until potatoes are tender. Yields 8 servings.

title: maggie's dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in oil; add remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles and add.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 375° in a covered casserole dish for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes more.
Makes a huge dish.

title: sun river sensation-chili
directions: Simmer green peppers, sweet onions and green onions with bacon for 20 minutes. Put kidney beans, chili con carne, ketchup and chili sauce in large casserole and combine with bacon, green peppers, sweet onions and green onions. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and add one pint of burgundy.
Return to oven and bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.
Add ground beef.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples, brown sugar and cinnamon in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and egg. Crumble and put over apples.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown and apples are done.

title: pineapple marshmallow dessert
directions: Cover bottom of buttered oblong pan with crumbs.
Dissolve marshmallows in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Let cool, then add Cool Whip and drain pineapple; mix well.
Pour filling into pan and top with additional crumbs.
Chill for several hours.
Cut into squares to serve.
Delicious and simple.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken for 30 minutes and debone. Place meat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Crush 1/2 bag chips; sprinkle on top of chicken. Add sliced Velveeta on top of chips. Blend both soups and Ro-Tel together. Pour this over cheese. Add last of 1/2 chips, crumbled on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave for 1 to 3 minutes on High until warmed.
Serve on buns or put cold mixture in bun, wrap in wax paper and warm in microwave 20 to 30 seconds for 1
or 2 1/2 to 3 minutes for 6 on High.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake according to directions on box.

title: flo's bread & butter pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers and onions in large jar, bowl or crock. Cover with weak salt water solution.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling point.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Simmer until good and hot - about 1/2 hour. May be kept in jar in refrigerator or canned.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, saute ground beef, mushrooms and onions in hot oil until browned; drain and add bouillon, water, wine, catsup and mustard.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Combine flour with cold water.
Slowly stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to
a boil.
Reduce heat; stir in sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: festive lasagna
directions: Coat eggplant slices with flour.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium heat; quickly cook eggplant in oil until lightly browned, adding more oil if necessary.
Drain eggplant on paper towels.
Spread 1 cup marinara sauce on bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish; top sauce with 3 lasagna noodles.
Combine Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, spinach, egg, basil, oregano, pepper and salt. Spread half of cheese mixture on noodles in baking pan.

Layer with half of eggplant slices, 1 cup marinara sauce, 3 lasagna noodles, remaining cheese mixture, remaining eggplant slices, 1 cup marinara sauce, 3 lasagna noodles, remaining 1 cup marinara sauce and remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand, covered, 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: talerina
directions: Saute vegetables in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients in layers, saving some cheese and olives to sprinkle on top.
Make sure noodles are covered with liquid. Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Turn to simmer and cook for approximately 30 minutes.
A 10-inch skillet works well for this. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: nana anker's spinach cheese appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes. Cool 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
May be frozen and reheated, as needed, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix cooking oil, sugar and whole eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: quiche
directions: Refrigerate pie shell for 1/2 hour.
In a bowl, combine soup, eggs and sour cream.
Toss flour with remaining ingredients; sprinkle over bottom of pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over vegetable and cheese mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 1 hour, or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: microwave date or raisin squares
directions: Combine fruit, water and lemon juice in a microwave bowl with vented cover.
Cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Fruit should be soft.
Let stand until cool.
Combine flour, rolled oats, sugar, salt, baking powder and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of crumbles in an 8-inch square pan.
Top with fruit.
Add remaining crumbles and pat down lightly.
Cook on Medium for 9 to 12 minutes.
Remove from microwave and cover with foil.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cool completely. Makes about 25 squares.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions using 4 eggs instead of 3 eggs.
Pour cake mix on top of coconut and nuts. Cream oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with whipped topping before serving.

title: sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar; cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar melts.
Continue cooking without stirring to "hard crack stage" (300°) or becomes very brittle when a drop is placed in cold water (without thermometer).
Remove from heat. Quickly stir in baking soda.
Pour into well-greased pan.
When cool and hard, break into pieces.
Excellent when coated with chocolate!

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon in electric frying pan until almost done.
Add onions and green pepper; cook in bacon grease until crisp-tender. Slowly spoon in prepared boiled potatoes and boiled eggs. Carefully toss and mix.
Add dried parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Splash with vinegar; stir and taste.
Keep adding vinegar until desired flavor is reached (some like more vinegar than others).
Gently toss until warmed through.
Serve warm.

title: beef egg roll filling
directions: Cook beef in large pan or wok until all the red color is gone. Add remainder of ingredients; steam about 3 to 5 minutes, just until cabbage is wilted.
Drain in colander and cool before filling the wrappers.
Fill wrappers (directions for filling on wrapper package).
Fry in peanut oil until brown.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Cream butter; beat in sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and alternately milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
May add chopped nuts or a walnut half to each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, then add flour and potato chips.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Dip into 10x sugar while warm.

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Beat 1 1/2 cups four and remaining ingredients in large bowl on low, scraping the bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes, still scraping the bowl.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn dough on a well floured cloth-covered board.
Roll around gently to cover with flour.
Roll gently 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.

title: rice casserole(serves 8)
directions: Cook rice per package directions.
When done, add oleo, corn with liquid and soup.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered.
Spread cheese over top, return to oven and melt.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Have spinach washed, dried and nicely chilled ahead of time and very near serving time add other ingredients.

title: mother's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar with baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough until firm enough to roll out on floured pastry cloth.
Roll a little sugar in on top of dough.
Cut with biscuit cutter or into fancy shapes.
Preheat oven at 425° and bake until brown on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Do not add any liquid other than the eggs and vanilla.

title: frosted toffee bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine oats, sugar and margarine; mix well. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool.
In a small heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips.
Spread over oat mixture; sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until chocolate sets.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend.
Add dry ingredients to peanut butter mixture.
Mix well.
Shape batter into small balls.
Place into ungreased mini muffin tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until they are just barely tender, not yet soft. Cut them into small cubes and combine them with the cottage cheese, sour cream, garlic, salt and scallions.
Turn the mixture into a buttered casserole and sprinkle the grated Cheddar cheese over the top.
Add a little paprika and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: low cholesterol whip topping
directions: Soften gelatin in water 5 minutes.
Stir powdered milk into skim milk in saucepan.
Heat to simmer and add softened gelatin, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add vanilla and sugar and chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat with mixer or rotary beater until very thick and light.
Approximately 6 calories per serving.
Diabetic substitution; about 1/4 cup nonfat or skim milk.

title: fruit curry
directions: Cut all fruit in half or fourths.
Drain.
Mix the sugar, flour and curry powder together and add to the fruit.
Dot the butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead of time and reheated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: um!  good potatoes
directions: Melt butter and soup; mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: basil shrimp fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a nonstick skillet, saute the onion, peppers and garlic in oil until tender. In a a small bowl, combine flour and milk until smooth. Add to vegetable mixture. Stir in the seasonings. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat; add shrimp and basil. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Drain pasta; place in a large bowl. Add shrimp mixture and toss to coat.

title: bavarian casserole(a combination of several recipes, serve with rye bread.)
directions: Salt and pepper pork pieces.
Heat Dutch oven.
Add 1 Tbsp. oil and lightly brown pork cubes.
Remove from pan and save.
Add rest of oil to Dutch oven if needed.
Brown onions, dill seed, caraway seeds and raisins over low heat about 20 minutes until onions have begun to caramelize. Then add 1 c stock and simmer until reduced a little.
Drain sauerkraut and add.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add pork cubes and spaetzle.
Add one c chicken stock if necessary.
Heat through making sure pork is cooked.
Hearty enough to be a main dish.
See Spaetzle recipe in Vegetables section of cookbook.

title: shreveport gumbo
directions: In large heavy skillet, combine flour and oil.
Cook over medium heat 25 to 30 minutes or until dark reddish-brown roux is formed; stir frequently first 15 minutes, or stir constantly last 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; immediately stir in onions, green pepper, celery and garlic until roux stops browning.
Return to heat; cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate icing for sheath cake
directions: Place margarine, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, being careful not to let scorch.
Then add sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Spread on cake.

title: 2-minute sweet cream biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix all ingredients until dough forms. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 1 dozen biscuits.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Be sure the cheese is melted.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool; cut into 1-inch squares.

title: holiday party punch
directions: Combine fruit juices with tea in punch bowl.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Float ice cubes in punch.
Add orange or lemon slices to punch.
Yields 3 1/2-quarts or 18 (6 oz.) servings.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in pieces and cook in salted, boiling water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Place bacon in skillet; simmer until it starts to brown.
Add onions and cook 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook 15 more minutes.
Combine mixtures.
Add crumbs and cheese in layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mad hatter meatballs
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add pepper and onion and cook.
Stir in chicken and rice soup, tomato soup and water; heat to boiling, then turn down heat and let simmer, stirring occasionally.

title: franke's chili dip
directions: Brown beef and saut with onions and garlic; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring often as cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat 400° oven.
Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Cook onion and beef until tender, no red.
Drain.
Season salt and pepper. Spread meat in dish.
Cover with soup and top with layer frozen Tater Tots.
Cook 45 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add spices to taste. Knead in enough flour until dough can be rolled out and made into thin layers (can use regular round cake pan as cutter, slicing each layer the same size).
Makes 8 to 9 layers.
Bake at 450° until browned.
Cook down apples; sweeten to taste.
Can add more spices. Put apples between layers as you stack them.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with pats of butter.
Sprinkle grated cheese and pimentos.
Bake for 90 minutes at 325°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine together for 1 minute, then add remainder of ingredients.
Stir it all up.
Drop little balls of dough on waxed paper with a teaspoon.
Let them get cool, then they are ready to eat.

title: frozen strawberry pineapple dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cool.
Add milk and pineapple and freeze.
